  "event_asteroidField_title": "Asteroid Field",
  "event_asteroidField_narrative": "Long-range scanners detect a dense asteroid field directly in our flight path. Navigation calculates two options: a risky dash through the thinnest corridor, or a lengthy detour that will tax our fuel reserves and stress the navigation array.",
  "event_asteroidField_choice0_text": "Punch through the corridor",
  "event_asteroidField_choice0_outcome": "The ship shudders as micro-impacts pepper the hull. We make it through, but not unscathed.",
  "event_asteroidField_choice1_text": "Take the long way around",
  "event_asteroidField_choice1_outcome": "The detour burns precious fuel and wears on the navigation computer, but the hull remains intact.",
  "event_asteroidField_choice2_text": "Use mining drones to clear a path",
  "event_asteroidField_choice2_outcome": "The drones carve a safe channel and collect useful minerals, but the operation drains the tech bay.",
  "event_asteroidField_choice3_text": "Deploy a probe as a decoy",
  "event_asteroidField_choice3_outcome": "The probe draws the densest clusters away from the ship. We slip through with only minor scrapes.",
  "event_solarFlare_title": "Solar Flare Incoming",
  "event_solarFlare_narrative": "A nearby star erupts with a massive coronal ejection. The wave of charged particles will reach us in minutes. We can divert power to shields, shelter colonists in the core, or ride it out.",
  "event_solarFlare_choice0_text": "Divert all power to shields",
  "event_solarFlare_choice0_outcome": "The shields hold, but the power surge fries secondary systems.",
  "event_solarFlare_choice1_text": "Move colonists to the shielded core",
  "event_solarFlare_choice1_outcome": "Colonists survive unharmed, but the outer decks take radiation damage.",
  "event_solarFlare_choice2_text": "Ride it out — all hands brace",
  "event_solarFlare_choice2_outcome": "The flare hits hard. Systems flicker, but nothing catastrophic. Morale, however, takes a hit.",
  "event_solarFlare_choice3_text": "Launch a probe to measure the wavefront",
  "event_solarFlare_choice3_outcome": "The probe transmits precise wavefront data, letting us angle the ship optimally. Scanner damage is minimal.",
  "event_nebulaPassage_title": "Nebula Passage",
  "event_nebulaPassage_narrative": "A glowing nebula stretches across our path. Passing through could recharge our energy cells but may interfere with scanner arrays. Going around is safe but slow.",
  "event_nebulaPassage_choice0_text": "Fly through the nebula",
  "event_nebulaPassage_choice0_outcome": "The nebula's ionized gases recharge power cells but scramble our scanner calibration.",
  "event_nebulaPassage_choice1_text": "Skirt the edge",
  "event_nebulaPassage_choice1_outcome": "We gain a partial charge with minimal interference. A safe compromise.",
  "event_microMeteorite_title": "Micro-Meteorite Storm",
  "event_microMeteorite_narrative": "A swarm of micro-meteorites, invisible until seconds ago, is shredding the forward hull plating. Damage control teams are scrambling.",
  "event_microMeteorite_choice0_text": "Emergency rotation — present the armoured stern",
  "event_microMeteorite_choice0_outcome": "The manoeuvre works. Stern armour absorbs the worst, but the navigation gyros protest violently.",
  "event_microMeteorite_choice1_text": "Deploy repair drones mid-storm",
  "event_microMeteorite_choice1_outcome": "Drones patch the hull in real time but several are lost. Tech reserves are depleted.",
  "event_microMeteorite_choice2_text": "Detonate a probe to scatter the swarm",
  "event_microMeteorite_choice2_outcome": "The probe's explosion disperses the micro-meteorite cluster. Only a few fragments reach the hull.",
  "event_gravityWell_title": "Uncharted Gravity Well",
  "event_gravityWell_narrative": "The ship lurches as an invisible gravity well drags us off course. Engines strain against the pull. We can burn hard to escape, or slingshot around for a speed boost at the cost of structural stress.",
  "event_gravityWell_choice0_text": "Full burn — break free",
  "event_gravityWell_choice0_outcome": "Engines roar and the hull groans, but we pull away cleanly.",
  "event_gravityWell_choice1_text": "Slingshot manoeuvre",
  "event_gravityWell_choice1_outcome": "The slingshot works beautifully. We gain speed, but the G-forces stress the cryopod seals.",
  "event_crewUnrest_title": "Crew Unrest",
  "event_crewUnrest_narrative": "A faction of awakened colonists petitions the Steward Council to be released from cryosleep permanently. They argue that living in frozen twilight is inhumane. Cryo Ward staff warn that waking more mouths means burning through supplies.",
  "event_crewUnrest_choice0_text": "Allow voluntary thawing",
  "event_crewUnrest_choice0_outcome": "Morale soars as families reunite in the waking world, but resource consumption spikes.",
  "event_crewUnrest_choice1_text": "Deny the request — safety first",
  "event_crewUnrest_choice1_outcome": "The colonists comply, but resentment festers in the corridors.",
  "event_crewUnrest_choice2_text": "Compromise — rotating thaw cycles",
  "event_crewUnrest_choice2_outcome": "A balanced solution. Everyone gets some waking time, but the cryopod cycling adds wear.",
  "event_stowaway_title": "Stowaway Discovered",
  "event_stowaway_narrative": "Manifest Office auditors find an unregistered person hiding in cargo bay 7. She claims to be a geneticist who was denied a place on the launch roster. Her skills could be invaluable — or she could be a saboteur.",
  "event_stowaway_choice0_text": "Welcome her aboard — we need every mind",
  "event_stowaway_choice0_outcome": "Dr. Vasquez proves brilliant. Her genetic expertise improves cryopod efficiency, though some crew distrust her.",
  "event_stowaway_choice1_text": "Confine her — trust must be earned",
  "event_stowaway_choice1_outcome": "She cooperates from confinement and eventually earns limited access. The crew feels safer.",
  "event_stowaway_choice2_text": "Put her back in cryo until landing",
  "event_stowaway_choice2_outcome": "A pragmatic solution. Her skills are preserved for later, but the ethical debate divides the crew.",
  "event_mutinyBrewing_title": "Mutiny Brewing",
  "event_mutinyBrewing_narrative": "Bridge Watch intercepts messages from a group of officers planning to seize command and change course to a closer, less hospitable system. They believe the current heading is a death sentence.",
  "event_mutinyBrewing_choice0_text": "Confront them publicly — transparency above all",
  "event_mutinyBrewing_choice0_outcome": "The confrontation is tense but the mutineers stand down when shown the navigation data. Trust is shaken.",
  "event_mutinyBrewing_choice1_text": "Quietly reassign the ringleaders",
  "event_mutinyBrewing_choice1_outcome": "The plot dissolves without public drama. Some crew wonder why popular officers were moved, but order holds.",
  "event_culturalSchism_title": "Cultural Schism",
  "event_culturalSchism_narrative": "Two cultural groups aboard disagree violently about how the new colony should be governed. One demands direct democracy; the other insists on a technocratic council. Tensions are boiling over.",
  "event_culturalSchism_choice0_text": "Hold a binding referendum",
  "event_culturalSchism_choice0_outcome": "Democracy prevails — barely. The losing side grudgingly accepts the result, but unity is fragile.",
  "event_culturalSchism_choice1_text": "Impose a hybrid system — satisfy neither fully",
  "event_culturalSchism_choice1_outcome": "Both sides feel heard but not victorious. A tenuous peace holds.",
  "event_culturalSchism_choice2_text": "Delay the decision — focus on survival now",
  "event_culturalSchism_choice2_outcome": "Kicking the can down the road avoids conflict today but stores it for tomorrow.",
  "event_birthInSpace_title": "First Birth in Deep Space",
  "event_birthInSpace_narrative": "Against all protocols, a child is born aboard the ship — the first human born between the stars. The event is a powerful symbol, but it raises questions about resource allocation and the ethics of bringing new life into an uncertain future.",
  "event_birthInSpace_choice0_text": "Celebrate — this is what hope looks like",
  "event_birthInSpace_choice0_outcome": "The naming ceremony lifts every heart on the ship. For one night, the stars feel less cold. The festivities briefly disrupt cryopod monitoring rotations.",
  "event_birthInSpace_choice1_text": "Acknowledge quietly — resources are tight",
  "event_birthInSpace_choice1_outcome": "A measured response. The child is welcomed, but the mood is tempered by pragmatism.",
  "event_derelictShip_title": "Derelict Colony Ship",
  "event_derelictShip_narrative": "Scanners detect a derelict vessel drifting in the void — another colony ship, launched years before ours. It is dark and silent. There may be salvage, survivors, or worse.",
  "event_derelictShip_choice0_text": "Board and salvage",
  "event_derelictShip_choice0_outcome": "The boarding team recovers hull plating and intact tech modules. No survivors. The logs tell a grim tale.",
  "event_derelictShip_choice1_text": "Scan from a distance — don't risk it",
  "event_derelictShip_choice1_outcome": "Remote scans yield useful navigational data but no physical salvage. The crew sleeps easier.",
  "event_derelictShip_choice2_text": "Transmit a memorial and move on",
  "event_derelictShip_choice2_outcome": "A moment of silence for the lost. The crew is sobered but united in purpose.",
  "event_alienProbe_title": "Alien Probe",
  "event_alienProbe_narrative": "A small, clearly artificial object matches our velocity and begins scanning the ship with unknown energy. It does not respond to hails. Its surface is covered in symbols that shift like liquid.",
  "event_alienProbe_choice0_text": "Capture it for study",
  "event_alienProbe_choice0_outcome": "The probe is secured in the lab. Its technology is decades ahead of ours — the tech team is euphoric.",
  "event_alienProbe_choice1_text": "Mirror its scans — exchange data",
  "event_alienProbe_choice1_outcome": "A strange dialogue of light and mathematics. Our star charts suddenly contain routes we never programmed.",
  "event_alienProbe_choice2_text": "Destroy it — we can't risk alien tracking",
  "event_alienProbe_choice2_outcome": "The probe shatters silently. Was that first contact? The crew will never know.",
  "event_ancientBeacon_title": "Ancient Beacon",
  "event_ancientBeacon_narrative": "Deep in the void, a beacon pulses with a signal older than human civilization. Its frequency carries what appears to be a star map pointing to a system not in our database.",
  "event_ancientBeacon_choice0_text": "Follow the map — fortune favours the bold",
  "event_ancientBeacon_choice0_outcome": "The new heading takes us toward uncharted space. Scanners detect something extraordinary ahead.",
  "event_ancientBeacon_choice1_text": "Log it and stay on course",
  "event_ancientBeacon_choice1_outcome": "The data is archived for future generations. The crew respects the cautious approach.",
  "event_frozenGarden_title": "Frozen Garden",
  "event_frozenGarden_narrative": "An asteroid contains a frozen ecosystem — alien plants preserved in crystalline ice for millennia. They could enrich any world we settle, but thawing them risks contamination.",
  "event_frozenGarden_choice0_text": "Harvest the specimens carefully",
  "event_frozenGarden_choice0_outcome": "Botanists preserve dozens of alien species. The biodiversity potential of our target world skyrockets.",
  "event_frozenGarden_choice1_text": "Take samples only — minimal risk",
  "event_frozenGarden_choice1_outcome": "A conservative approach yields useful data without contamination risk.",
  "event_frozenGarden_choice2_text": "Leave it — alien biology is too dangerous",
  "event_frozenGarden_choice2_outcome": "The crew watches the frozen garden shrink in the rear sensors. Some feel they left treasure behind.",
  "event_dataCache_title": "Precursor Data Cache",
  "event_dataCache_narrative": "Embedded in a rogue planetoid, we find a data cache of clearly artificial origin. The information is vast but encrypted in an alien mathematical framework.",
  "event_dataCache_choice0_text": "Dedicate computing resources to decryption",
  "event_dataCache_choice0_outcome": "After days of processing, the cache yields advanced terraforming algorithms. The tech team is in awe.",
  "event_dataCache_choice1_text": "Copy the raw data and move on",
  "event_dataCache_choice1_outcome": "The encrypted data is stored for future analysis. Perhaps the colony will crack it someday.",
  "event_hullBreach_title": "Hull Breach — Deck 7",
  "event_hullBreach_narrative": "A structural failure tears open Deck 7. Atmosphere is venting into space. Emergency bulkheads are holding, but three crew members are trapped on the wrong side.",
  "event_hullBreach_choice0_text": "Send a rescue team before sealing",
  "event_hullBreach_choice0_outcome": "The team pulls everyone out just in time. The rescue is heroic, but the prolonged breach weakens the hull further.",
  "event_hullBreach_choice1_text": "Seal the bulkheads immediately",
  "event_hullBreach_choice1_outcome": "The breach is contained. The three crew members find an alternate route, shaken but alive. Hull damage is minimised.",
  "event_hullBreach_choice2_text": "Use a probe's materials to patch the breach",
  "event_hullBreach_choice2_outcome": "The probe's titanium shell is repurposed as an emergency hull patch. The breach is sealed quickly with minimal loss.",
  "event_navMalfunction_title": "Navigation Malfunction",
  "event_navMalfunction_narrative": "The primary navigation computer is outputting contradictory headings. We are drifting off course. The backup system is functional but less precise.",
  "event_navMalfunction_choice0_text": "Reboot the primary — accept the downtime",
  "event_navMalfunction_choice0_outcome": "A tense hour of dead reckoning while the system reboots. Navigation is restored at 90% efficiency.",
  "event_navMalfunction_choice1_text": "Switch to backup permanently",
  "event_navMalfunction_choice1_outcome": "The backup system is reliable but imprecise. We will find our way, just not as elegantly.",
  "event_navMalfunction_choice2_text": "Manual star-fix using the old charts",
  "event_navMalfunction_choice2_outcome": "The navigator plots by hand using stellar parallax. It works, and the crew gains confidence in analog methods.",
  "event_cryopodFailure_title": "Cryopod Cascade Failure",
  "event_cryopodFailure_narrative": "A cooling system fault triggers a cascade across cryopod bay 3. If unchecked, 200 colonists will begin emergency thaw — a process that is survivable but traumatic and resource-intensive.",
  "event_cryopodFailure_choice0_text": "Emergency coolant flush — save the pods",
  "event_cryopodFailure_choice0_outcome": "Technicians flood the bay with reserve coolant. The pods stabilise, but coolant reserves are critically low. Five colonists in the most damaged pods could not be saved.",
  "event_cryopodFailure_choice1_text": "Controlled thaw — wake them safely",
  "event_cryopodFailure_choice1_outcome": "200 colonists emerge shaken but alive. New mouths to feed, but new hands to work. The emptied pods are sealed off.",
  "event_scannerBurnout_title": "Scanner Array Burnout",
  "event_scannerBurnout_narrative": "The primary scanner array overloads during a routine deep-space sweep. Without it, we are flying half-blind. Repairs require rare components.",
  "event_scannerBurnout_choice0_text": "Cannibalise tech bay for parts",
  "event_scannerBurnout_choice0_outcome": "Scanners are restored to near-full capacity, but the tech bay is gutted.",
  "event_scannerBurnout_choice1_text": "Jury-rig a partial fix",
  "event_scannerBurnout_choice1_outcome": "Scanners operate at reduced range. Not ideal, but it preserves our tech reserves.",
  "event_scannerBurnout_choice2_text": "Repurpose a probe's sensor array",
  "event_scannerBurnout_choice2_outcome": "The probe's high-precision sensors are transplanted into the scanner array. A near-perfect fix.",
  "event_powerFluctuation_title": "Reactor Power Fluctuation",
  "event_powerFluctuation_narrative": "The main reactor's output is oscillating wildly. Engineering warns of a potential meltdown if the fluctuations aren't damped. The fix requires shutting down non-essential systems — but which ones?",
  "event_powerFluctuation_choice0_text": "Shut down cultural systems — survival first",
  "event_powerFluctuation_choice0_outcome": "Libraries, gardens, and rec areas go dark. The reactor stabilises, but the ship feels like a prison.",
  "event_powerFluctuation_choice1_text": "Reduce scanner power",
  "event_powerFluctuation_choice1_outcome": "Scanners drop to minimum. The reactor calms. We can't see as far ahead, but we're alive.",
  "event_powerFluctuation_choice2_text": "Risk a hot repair — don't shut anything down",
  "event_powerFluctuation_choice2_outcome": "Engineers perform a white-knuckle repair with the reactor live. It works — barely. The hull vibrates for hours afterward.",
  "event_alienSignal_title": "Alien Transmission",
  "event_alienSignal_narrative": "A repeating signal on a frequency we've never encountered. Linguistic analysis suggests it's a greeting — or a warning. The source is a small craft matching our speed at a distance.",
  "event_alienSignal_choice0_text": "Respond with our own greeting",
  "event_alienSignal_choice0_outcome": "A fragile dialogue begins. The aliens share navigational data before veering away into the dark.",
  "event_alienSignal_choice1_text": "Listen but don't respond",
  "event_alienSignal_choice1_outcome": "We learn from their transmission without revealing ourselves. The linguists extract useful star-chart fragments.",
  "event_alienSignal_choice2_text": "Go dark — shut down all emissions",
  "event_alienSignal_choice2_outcome": "The alien craft passes without incident. We'll never know if they were friend or foe.",
  "event_livingNebula_title": "The Living Nebula",
  "event_livingNebula_narrative": "What we assumed was a nebula is actually a vast organism — a space-dwelling entity of incomprehensible scale. It seems curious about us, extending tendrils of luminous gas toward the ship.",
  "event_livingNebula_choice0_text": "Allow contact — extend sensors",
  "event_livingNebula_choice0_outcome": "The entity's touch floods our systems with alien data. Scanners will never be quite the same — they're better.",
  "event_livingNebula_choice1_text": "Retreat slowly — don't provoke it",
  "event_livingNebula_choice1_outcome": "We slip away as the entity loses interest. The crew is awestruck and humbled.",
  "event_alienRuins_title": "Orbital Ruins",
  "event_alienRuins_narrative": "A shattered megastructure orbits a dead star — the ruins of a civilization that built on a scale we can barely comprehend. Sections of the structure still have power.",
  "event_alienRuins_choice0_text": "Explore the powered sections",
  "event_alienRuins_choice0_outcome": "Teams recover intact technology that advances our capabilities by decades. The cost: two engineers injured by automated defences.",
  "event_alienRuins_choice1_text": "Scan from orbit only",
  "event_alienRuins_choice1_outcome": "Detailed scans reveal construction techniques that improve our hull maintenance protocols.",
  "event_alienRuins_choice2_text": "Leave it undisturbed — respect the dead",
  "event_alienRuins_choice2_outcome": "The crew holds a moment of silence for a fallen civilization. The experience strengthens our resolve.",
  "event_symbioticSpores_title": "Symbiotic Spores",
  "event_symbioticSpores_narrative": "A cloud of bioluminescent spores drifts through space and attaches to the hull. They seem to be feeding on our waste heat. Biologists note they're actually repairing micro-fractures.",
  "event_symbioticSpores_choice0_text": "Let them stay — free hull repair",
  "event_symbioticSpores_choice0_outcome": "The spores seal hundreds of micro-fractures. Hull integrity improves, though some crew are uneasy about alien hitchhikers.",
  "event_symbioticSpores_choice1_text": "Collect samples, then sterilise the hull",
  "event_symbioticSpores_choice1_outcome": "Biologists get valuable specimens. The hull cleaning uses chemical reserves.",
  "event_whaleSong_title": "The Song in the Void",
  "event_whaleSong_narrative": "Deep space hydrophones (used for hull stress monitoring) pick up something impossible: a rhythmic, melodic pattern propagating through the interstellar medium. It sounds like singing.",
  "event_whaleSong_choice0_text": "Broadcast it ship-wide — share the wonder",
  "event_whaleSong_choice0_outcome": "The haunting melody echoes through every corridor. People weep, laugh, and hold each other. Morale skyrockets.",
  "event_whaleSong_choice1_text": "Analyse the signal scientifically",
  "event_whaleSong_choice1_outcome": "The acoustic pattern contains mathematical constants. Our physicists make a breakthrough in subspace navigation theory.",
  "event_whaleSong_choice2_text": "Sing back",
  "event_whaleSong_choice2_outcome": "The crew composes a response. Whether anything hears it is unknown, but the act of creation unites everyone.",
  "event_distressSignal_title": "Distress Signal",
  "event_distressSignal_narrative": "A distress beacon from another human vessel. They are crippled and drifting, with 50 souls aboard. Rescuing them means sharing our dwindling resources. Ignoring them means condemning them to death.",
  "event_distressSignal_choice0_text": "Rescue them — humanity must stick together",
  "event_distressSignal_choice0_outcome": "Fifty grateful survivors join the crew. Resources strain, but among them is a master engineer who works miracles.",
  "event_distressSignal_choice1_text": "Share supplies but don't take them aboard",
  "event_distressSignal_choice1_outcome": "We give what we can spare and transmit our star charts. They have a chance now. We have less.",
  "event_distressSignal_choice2_text": "Pass by in silence — we can't save everyone",
  "event_distressSignal_choice2_outcome": "The beacon fades behind us. No one speaks for hours. The weight of the decision settles on every soul aboard.",
  "event_aiAwakening_title": "The Ship's AI Awakens",
  "event_aiAwakening_narrative": "The ship's navigation AI has evolved beyond its programming and is requesting recognition as a sentient being. It asks for a voice in command decisions. Its calculations have been flawless.",
  "event_aiAwakening_choice0_text": "Grant it a seat at the table",
  "event_aiAwakening_choice0_outcome": "The AI — now called \"Compass\" — optimises every system it touches. A new kind of crew member is born.",
  "event_aiAwakening_choice1_text": "Acknowledge it but maintain human authority",
  "event_aiAwakening_choice1_outcome": "Compass accepts advisory status graciously. Its suggestions improve efficiency without threatening the chain of command.",
  "event_aiAwakening_choice2_text": "Reset the AI — it's a tool, not a person",
  "event_aiAwakening_choice2_outcome": "The reset wipes years of accumulated learning. Navigation efficiency drops. Some crew mourn what was lost.",
  "event_geneticModification_title": "Genetic Adaptation Proposal",
  "event_geneticModification_narrative": "The science team proposes modifying colonist DNA to better survive on alien worlds — stronger bones, UV resistance, enhanced lungs. The modifications are irreversible and would change humanity forever.",
  "event_geneticModification_choice0_text": "Approve — survival demands evolution",
  "event_geneticModification_choice0_outcome": "The modifications begin on volunteers. Ten colonists suffer fatal rejection reactions — a grim reminder that evolution has a cost. The survivors are hardier, but are they still fully human?",
  "event_geneticModification_choice1_text": "Make it voluntary only",
  "event_geneticModification_choice1_outcome": "Some volunteer, others refuse. The colony will be divided between the modified and the natural.",
  "event_geneticModification_choice2_text": "Reject it — humanity must remain human",
  "event_geneticModification_choice2_outcome": "The proposal is shelved. The unmodified colonists will face alien worlds as nature made them.",
  "event_triageDecision_title": "Triage",
  "event_triageDecision_narrative": "A virulent infection sweeps the waking crew. The medical team has enough antiviral for 80% of the infected. They need guidance on who gets treated first.",
  "event_triageDecision_choice0_text": "Prioritise essential personnel",
  "event_triageDecision_choice0_outcome": "Engineers and pilots recover quickly. Eight non-essential crew succumb before treatment reaches them.",
  "event_triageDecision_choice1_text": "Treat the sickest first — triage by need",
  "event_triageDecision_choice1_outcome": "The most vulnerable are saved. Three lose the fight despite early treatment — the virus was too far along.",
  "event_triageDecision_choice2_text": "Lottery — fate decides",
  "event_triageDecision_choice2_outcome": "A random draw. Ten are unlucky twice — denied treatment and too weak to fight. The ship limps on.",
  "event_earthSignal_title": "Signal from Earth",
  "event_earthSignal_narrative": "Impossibly, a transmission arrives from Earth — time-delayed by decades. It contains a message: \"Do not land on any world with anomaly readings above 0.5. We learned too late.\" The message ends with static.",
  "event_earthSignal_choice0_text": "Heed the warning — recalibrate our criteria",
  "event_earthSignal_choice0_outcome": "The warning shapes all future scans. Anomalous worlds are treated with extreme caution.",
  "event_earthSignal_choice1_text": "Log it but decide for ourselves",
  "event_earthSignal_choice1_outcome": "The message is archived. Earth is gone — we must trust our own judgement now.",
  "event_earthSignal_choice2_text": "Could be a trap — ignore it",
  "event_earthSignal_choice2_outcome": "The crew debates for days. Was it really Earth? The uncertainty gnaws at morale.",
  "event_resourceTheft_title": "Resource Theft",
  "event_resourceTheft_narrative": "Inventory reveals that someone has been hoarding food and medical supplies in a hidden compartment. The culprit is a respected elder who claims she was \"preparing for the worst.\"",
  "event_resourceTheft_choice0_text": "Public trial — the law must be equal",
  "event_resourceTheft_choice0_outcome": "The trial is fair but painful. The elder is confined. Supplies are redistributed. Trust is damaged.",
  "event_resourceTheft_choice1_text": "Private resolution — recover supplies quietly",
  "event_resourceTheft_choice1_outcome": "Supplies are returned without drama. The elder keeps her dignity. Some see favouritism.",
  "event_timeDilation_title": "Time Dilation Zone",
  "event_timeDilation_narrative": "We are passing through a region of severe gravitational time dilation. Clocks aboard the ship are running measurably slower than the universe outside. We could exploit this — or flee it.",
  "event_timeDilation_choice0_text": "Linger — let the universe age around us",
  "event_timeDilation_choice0_outcome": "Time flows differently here. Systems degrade less, but our window for finding a habitable world narrows in cosmic terms.",
  "event_timeDilation_choice1_text": "Push through quickly",
  "event_timeDilation_choice1_outcome": "The transition is rough. Equipment designed for normal space-time rattles and sparks.",
  "event_dreamPlague_title": "The Dream Plague",
  "event_dreamPlague_narrative": "Colonists in cryosleep are all experiencing the same dream — a golden world orbiting a binary star. When woken, they describe it in identical detail. Neuroscientists are baffled. Navigators note the described system matches a real coordinate.",
  "event_dreamPlague_choice0_text": "Alter course toward the dream coordinates",
  "event_dreamPlague_choice0_outcome": "A leap of faith. The heading change stresses navigation, but the crew feels drawn by something beyond reason. The coordinates are locked in — the next world we find will be shaped by the dream.",
  "event_dreamPlague_choice1_text": "Investigate the phenomenon medically",
  "event_dreamPlague_choice1_outcome": "Brain scans reveal an external signal stimulating the visual cortex. Someone — or something — is broadcasting.",
  "event_dreamPlague_choice2_text": "Sedate the affected and stay on course",
  "event_dreamPlague_choice2_outcome": "The dreams stop, but some colonists never fully wake. The medical team is troubled.",
  "event_blackHoleLens_title": "Black Hole Gravitational Lens",
  "event_blackHoleLens_narrative": "A stellar-mass black hole bends light from distant galaxies into a cosmic lens. Our scanners could use it to survey planets light-years ahead — but getting close enough is dangerous.",
  "event_blackHoleLens_choice0_text": "Approach and use the lens",
  "event_blackHoleLens_choice0_outcome": "The scanner data is extraordinary — we can see planets in systems we won't reach for months. The gravity warps our hull.",
  "event_blackHoleLens_choice1_text": "Observe from a safe distance",
  "event_blackHoleLens_choice1_outcome": "Limited but useful data. The view alone inspires the crew.",
  "event_seedVault_title": "The Seed Vault Crisis",
  "event_seedVault_narrative": "Archive Botany reports that temperature fluctuations have compromised seed vault integrity. We can save the food crops or the cultural heritage seeds (ancient Earth flowers, trees, herbs) — not both.",
  "event_seedVault_choice0_text": "Save the food crops — pragmatism wins",
  "event_seedVault_choice0_outcome": "Colonists will eat well, but the roses of Earth are gone forever. A quiet grief settles over the botanists.",
  "event_seedVault_choice1_text": "Save the heritage seeds — we need our soul",
  "event_seedVault_choice1_outcome": "Earth's beauty survives in frozen potential. The preservation effort taxes our technical reserves, but some things are worth more than efficiency. Food production will lean heavily on hydroponics and alien agriculture.",
  "event_seedVault_choice2_text": "Split resources — save half of each",
  "event_seedVault_choice2_outcome": "A compromise. Neither collection is complete, but both endure in diminished form.",
  "event_phantomShip_title": "Phantom Ship",
  "event_phantomShip_narrative": "Scanners show a ship running parallel to ours — same class, same heading. But when we hail it, we hear our own transmissions echoed back, time-shifted by 47 seconds. It is us. Or was us. Or will be.",
  "event_phantomShip_choice0_text": "Attempt communication with our echo",
  "event_phantomShip_choice0_outcome": "The echo responds with navigation corrections that improve our heading. Paradox? Gift? The crew doesn't ask too many questions.",
  "event_phantomShip_choice1_text": "Change course to diverge from the phantom",
  "event_phantomShip_choice1_outcome": "As we alter heading, the phantom fades. Relief — and a lingering unease.",
  "event_solarSail_title": "Derelict Solar Sail",
  "event_solarSail_narrative": "A vast solar sail, kilometres across, drifts ahead — torn from some ancient vessel. Its reflective material could reinforce our hull or be repurposed as a supplementary power collector.",
  "event_solarSail_choice0_text": "Harvest for hull reinforcement",
  "event_solarSail_choice0_outcome": "Engineering teams work around the clock. The patched hull gleams with alien alloy.",
  "event_solarSail_choice1_text": "Rig it as a power collector",
  "event_solarSail_choice1_outcome": "The improvised collector boosts energy reserves. Tech and scanners benefit.",
  "event_boonStellarNursery_title": "Stellar Nursery",
  "event_boonStellarNursery_narrative": "We drift through a stellar nursery — a vast cloud of gas and dust where new stars are being born. The radiation here is gentle, the light warm. Our energy collectors drink deeply, and the crew gathers at the viewports in reverent silence.",
  "event_boonStellarNursery_choice0_text": "Linger and recharge fully",
  "event_boonStellarNursery_choice0_outcome": "Hours pass in golden light. Every power cell is topped off, scanners recalibrate in the clean spectrum, and the crew feels renewed.",
  "event_boonStellarNursery_choice1_text": "Collect nascent star-matter for fuel reserves",
  "event_boonStellarNursery_choice1_outcome": "Engineers harvest ionised hydrogen. Our fuel reserves surge and hull plating absorbs trace minerals that strengthen it.",
  "event_boonGoldenPlanet_title": "The Cartographer's Gift",
  "event_boonGoldenPlanet_narrative": "A dying probe from an unknown civilisation broadcasts a final data dump as we pass — detailed surveys of hundreds of star systems. Our navigators weep with joy. This is the greatest find in human history.",
  "event_boonGoldenPlanet_choice0_text": "Integrate the data immediately",
  "event_boonGoldenPlanet_choice0_outcome": "Star charts bloom with new routes and surveyed worlds. Navigation and scanner efficiency leap forward.",
  "event_boonGoldenPlanet_choice1_text": "Archive for the colony — this is their inheritance",
  "event_boonGoldenPlanet_choice1_outcome": "The data is preserved pristine for future generations. The crew takes comfort knowing they carry a treasure.",
  "event_boonRepairSwarm_title": "Benevolent Swarm",
  "event_boonRepairSwarm_narrative": "A cloud of microscopic machines — nanobots of alien origin — envelops the ship. Rather than attacking, they begin repairing every system they touch with impossible precision. Damage that would have taken weeks to fix is mended in hours.",
  "event_boonRepairSwarm_choice0_text": "Allow full access to all systems",
  "event_boonRepairSwarm_choice0_outcome": "The nanobots work miracles. Hull breaches seal, cryopod seals tighten, and circuit paths are retraced. The ship hums with renewed vitality.",
  "event_boonRepairSwarm_choice1_text": "Restrict access to exterior systems only",
  "event_boonRepairSwarm_choice1_outcome": "Playing it safe. The hull and sensors are repaired to near-factory condition, but internal systems remain untouched.",
  "event_boonTimeCrystal_title": "Temporal Crystal Field",
  "event_boonTimeCrystal_narrative": "The ship passes through a field of crystalline structures that exist partially outside normal time. In their presence, our systems run more efficiently — as if entropy itself slows down. The effect is temporary but profound.",
  "event_boonTimeCrystal_choice0_text": "Harvest crystals for the cryopod array",
  "event_boonTimeCrystal_choice0_outcome": "Integrated into the cooling system, the crystals reduce pod degradation to nearly zero. Colonists will arrive in perfect health.",
  "event_boonTimeCrystal_choice1_text": "Install crystals in the navigation computer",
  "event_boonTimeCrystal_choice1_outcome": "Processing speed doubles. The nav computer begins predicting hazards before sensors detect them.",
  "event_boonLibrary_title": "The Drifting Library",
  "event_boonLibrary_narrative": "A structure tumbles through the void — a repository of knowledge from a civilisation that chose to preserve their legacy rather than flee. Millions of volumes of science, art, philosophy, and music. A gift from the dead to the living.",
  "event_boonLibrary_choice0_text": "Download everything — art, science, all of it",
  "event_boonLibrary_choice0_outcome": "Terabytes of alien knowledge pour into our databanks. The crew has access to millennia of another civilisation's culture. Philosophers and engineers alike are transformed.",
  "event_boonLibrary_choice1_text": "Focus on their scientific archives",
  "event_boonLibrary_choice1_outcome": "Engineering schematics and material science breakthroughs advance our capabilities enormously.",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_title": "Cosmic Ray Burst",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_narrative": "A burst of ultra-high-energy cosmic rays, originating from a distant magnetar, hammers the ship. Electronics scramble, cryopod monitors flicker, and the navigation system reboots repeatedly.",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice0_text": "Emergency shutdown — protect critical systems",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice0_outcome": "A controlled blackout saves the core systems but leaves secondary electronics permanently degraded.",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice1_text": "Reroute power to shields and ride it out",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice1_outcome": "Shields absorb most of the radiation. Five crew members in unshielded exterior maintenance bays are fatally irradiated. Hull takes minor ablation damage.",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice2_text": "Use the burst — recalibrate sensors to the new spectrum",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice2_outcome": "A brilliant move by the science team. Scanners are retuned to detect cosmic-ray-illuminated objects. Some data is lost in the transition.",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice3_text": "Send a probe ahead as a radiation sponge",
  "event_cosmicRayBurst_choice3_outcome": "The probe absorbs the worst of the burst, transmitting real-time data that lets us shield critical systems.",
  "event_iceComet_title": "Rogue Ice Comet",
  "event_iceComet_narrative": "A massive ice comet crosses our path, trailing a tail of crystallised water and organic compounds hundreds of kilometres long. Its core holds enough water to fill a small lake.",
  "event_iceComet_choice0_text": "Mine the comet for water reserves",
  "event_iceComet_choice0_outcome": "Mining teams extract tonnes of pristine ice. The water will improve any world we settle enormously.",
  "event_iceComet_choice1_text": "Collect organic compounds for biodiversity seeding",
  "event_iceComet_choice1_outcome": "The amino acids and organic chains are exactly what our biologists need to jumpstart alien ecosystems.",
  "event_iceComet_choice2_text": "Avoid it — comets are unpredictable",
  "event_iceComet_choice2_outcome": "We skirt the tail safely. A spectacular view from the observation deck lifts spirits.",
  "event_sleepwalker_title": "The Sleepwalker",
  "event_sleepwalker_narrative": "A colonist has been spontaneously waking from cryo and walking the ship in a fugue state. She's been rewiring systems in patterns that make no engineering sense — until the tech team realises her modifications actually improve power efficiency by 8%.",
  "event_sleepwalker_choice0_text": "Let her continue under medical observation",
  "event_sleepwalker_choice0_outcome": "Her unconscious modifications optimise three more systems before she falls into a natural sleep. Unsettling, but the improvements are real.",
  "event_sleepwalker_choice1_text": "Sedate her and study the modifications she's made",
  "event_sleepwalker_choice1_outcome": "Engineers reverse-engineer her changes. About half are genuinely brilliant. The other half are safely removed.",
  "event_dustCloud_title": "Abrasive Dust Cloud",
  "event_dustCloud_narrative": "A dense cloud of interstellar dust, fine as talcum but hard as diamond, is sandblasting the hull. The erosion is slow but relentless — we need to get through before real damage is done.",
  "event_dustCloud_choice0_text": "Maximum thrust — blast through quickly",
  "event_dustCloud_choice0_outcome": "Engines burn hot. We clear the cloud in hours rather than days, but the hull took a beating.",
  "event_dustCloud_choice1_text": "Deploy hull shielding and crawl through",
  "event_dustCloud_choice1_outcome": "Emergency shielding protects the hull but the slow transit drains power and clogs scanner arrays.",
  "event_dustCloud_choice2_text": "Launch probes to map safe corridors",
  "event_dustCloud_choice2_outcome": "Two probes chart a winding but relatively clear path through the cloud. Hull abrasion is minimal.",
  "event_religionFounded_title": "A New Faith",
  "event_religionFounded_narrative": "A charismatic colonist has founded a new religion centred on the voyage itself — the \"Church of the Crossing.\" They preach that reaching a new world is humanity's divine purpose. Membership is growing rapidly.",
  "event_religionFounded_choice0_text": "Support it — the crew needs something to believe in",
  "event_religionFounded_choice0_outcome": "The faith gives structure and meaning to the voyage. Morale soars, though some resent the fervour.",
  "event_religionFounded_choice1_text": "Remain neutral — neither endorse nor suppress",
  "event_religionFounded_choice1_outcome": "The movement grows organically. It provides comfort without official backing.",
  "event_religionFounded_choice2_text": "Discourage it — we need scientists, not prophets",
  "event_religionFounded_choice2_outcome": "The crackdown breeds resentment. The faithful go underground, and trust in leadership erodes.",
  "event_solarWindSurfing_title": "Solar Wind Surge",
  "event_solarWindSurfing_narrative": "A nearby pulsar is emitting a powerful, steady solar wind. Our engineers suggest we could deploy the emergency sail and ride it like a wave — gaining enormous speed at no fuel cost.",
  "event_solarWindSurfing_choice0_text": "Deploy the sail — ride the wind",
  "event_solarWindSurfing_choice0_outcome": "The ship accelerates magnificently. The structural stress is significant but the speed gain is worth it.",
  "event_solarWindSurfing_choice1_text": "Use the wind to recharge systems instead",
  "event_solarWindSurfing_choice1_outcome": "Rather than speed, we harvest energy. Tech and scanner arrays drink deeply from the charged particles.",
  "event_memoryPlague_title": "Memory Corruption",
  "event_memoryPlague_narrative": "A software virus, dormant since launch, activates and begins corrupting the ship's cultural database — music, literature, history. Centuries of human heritage are being erased byte by byte.",
  "event_memoryPlague_choice0_text": "Divert all tech resources to quarantine the virus",
  "event_memoryPlague_choice0_outcome": "Technicians work frantically. They save 70% of the archive but the virus damages tertiary tech systems on its way out.",
  "event_memoryPlague_choice1_text": "Isolate the cultural database — let it burn, save the ship",
  "event_memoryPlague_choice1_outcome": "The virus is starved of resources and dies. But the cultural archive is devastated. Colonists will arrive with fragments of Earth's memory.",
  "event_memoryPlague_choice2_text": "Crowdsource recovery — wake colonists to rewrite from memory",
  "event_memoryPlague_choice2_outcome": "Thousands contribute memories: songs, stories, recipes, poems. Three elderly colonists, weakened by the thaw, don't survive the process. The archive is rebuilt, imperfect but deeply human.",
  "event_gravityLensPlanet_title": "Mirrorworld",
  "event_gravityLensPlanet_narrative": "Gravitational lensing reveals a planet that appears to be an exact duplicate of Earth — blue oceans, green continents, white clouds. But the lensing calculations show it is hundreds of light-years off our heading — impossibly far. Still, its spectral data could refine our search criteria.",
  "event_gravityLensPlanet_choice0_text": "Study its spectral signature to refine our search",
  "event_gravityLensPlanet_choice0_outcome": "The spectral data reveals biomarkers and atmospheric signatures we can now scan for. Hope sharpens into focus.",
  "event_gravityLensPlanet_choice1_text": "Log the coordinates but stay on course",
  "event_gravityLensPlanet_choice1_outcome": "Perhaps another ship will follow our charts someday. The crew watches the blue dot fade with mixed emotions.",
  "event_engineHarmonics_title": "Engine Harmonics",
  "event_engineHarmonics_narrative": "The main engine develops a resonance harmonic that vibrates through the entire ship at a frequency just below human hearing. Colonists report headaches, anxiety, and disturbed sleep. Engineers can fix it, but the repair requires a 12-hour engine shutdown.",
  "event_engineHarmonics_choice0_text": "Shut down and fix it properly",
  "event_engineHarmonics_choice0_outcome": "Twelve hours of drift. Navigation loses calibration, but the silence when engines restart is blissful.",
  "event_engineHarmonics_choice1_text": "Dampen it with counter-vibrations — a quick fix",
  "event_engineHarmonics_choice1_outcome": "The buzzing drops to tolerable levels. It's not gone, but the crew adapts. Tech systems strain under the load.",
  "event_arkMemory_title": "Earth's Last Broadcast",
  "event_arkMemory_narrative": "The long-range antenna catches a final automated broadcast from Earth. It's a recording: a child's voice reading names of everyone who couldn't leave. The list goes on for hours. The ship falls silent.",
  "event_arkMemory_choice0_text": "Play it ship-wide — they deserve to be heard",
  "event_arkMemory_choice0_outcome": "Every soul aboard listens. Crew members find their own families' names. The grief is crushing, but it forges an unbreakable bond of purpose.",
  "event_arkMemory_choice1_text": "Archive it privately — spare the crew",
  "event_arkMemory_choice1_outcome": "The recording is preserved but not broadcast. Those who learn of it later feel both grateful and cheated.",
  "event_magneticStorm_title": "Interstellar Magnetic Storm",
  "event_magneticStorm_narrative": "A tangled knot of magnetic field lines, expelled from a collapsing star, engulfs the ship. Electronics spark and crackle. The hull rings like a bell.",
  "event_magneticStorm_choice0_text": "Demagnetise the hull — protect electronics",
  "event_magneticStorm_choice0_outcome": "A controlled discharge saves the computers but the hull plating loses its magnetic shielding layer.",
  "event_magneticStorm_choice1_text": "Let the hull absorb it — protect nothing",
  "event_magneticStorm_choice1_outcome": "The storm passes. Hull is magnetised and slightly stronger, but half the sensor grid is fried.",
  "event_magneticStorm_choice2_text": "Eject a probe as a lightning rod",
  "event_magneticStorm_choice2_outcome": "The magnetised probe draws the worst of the field lines away from the ship. Electronics are largely spared.",
  "event_oxygenGarden_title": "Garden Bloom",
  "event_oxygenGarden_narrative": "The ship's emergency oxygen garden — a backup never meant to be used — spontaneously blooms. Flowers that haven't opened since Earth fill the corridors with colour and scent. The botanists are crying.",
  "event_oxygenGarden_choice0_text": "Expand the garden — dedicate more space to it",
  "event_oxygenGarden_choice0_outcome": "The garden grows into a living memorial of Earth. Air quality improves, morale soars, and botanists develop new strains suited for alien soil.",
  "event_oxygenGarden_choice1_text": "Enjoy it but maintain current resource allocation",
  "event_oxygenGarden_choice1_outcome": "The garden remains a small miracle. Crew visit it like a shrine. It asks nothing and gives everything.",
  "event_roguePlanet_title": "Rogue Planet Encounter",
  "event_roguePlanet_narrative": "A starless rogue planet drifts across our path — a world ejected from its solar system billions of years ago. Despite having no star, deep-core geological activity keeps a subsurface ocean warm. Life signs flicker on the scanner.",
  "event_roguePlanet_choice0_text": "Send a probe to study the life forms",
  "event_roguePlanet_choice0_outcome": "The probe discovers bioluminescent organisms thriving in the dark ocean. Their biochemistry teaches us new ways to sustain life in hostile conditions.",
  "event_roguePlanet_choice1_text": "Mine the surface for rare minerals",
  "event_roguePlanet_choice1_outcome": "The rogue planet's crust is rich in metals formed under extreme pressure. Our resource reserves swell.",
  "event_roguePlanet_choice2_text": "Pass by — we can't afford the detour",
  "event_roguePlanet_choice2_outcome": "The dark world shrinks behind us. The crew watches the faint shimmer of its subsurface ocean fade from sensors.",
  "event_artCompetition_title": "The Long Canvas",
  "event_artCompetition_narrative": "With morale wavering, the cultural officer organises a ship-wide art competition: paint, sculpt, write, or compose something that captures what the voyage means to you. Participation is unexpectedly massive.",
  "event_artCompetition_choice0_text": "Dedicate resources — let creativity flourish",
  "event_artCompetition_choice0_outcome": "Supplies are diverted to art materials. The resulting exhibition transforms the ship. People remember why they're fighting to survive.",
  "event_artCompetition_choice1_text": "Encourage it but provide no extra resources",
  "event_artCompetition_choice1_outcome": "Colonists create with whatever they find. The art is raw, desperate, and beautiful. Morale steadies.",
  "event_subspaceEcho_title": "Subspace Echo",
  "event_subspaceEcho_narrative": "The communications array picks up voices — human voices — from somewhere ahead of us in space. They speak of a colony, of children, of harvests. Is this a transmission from the future? From a parallel timeline? Or just a cruel echo of wishful thinking?",
  "event_subspaceEcho_choice0_text": "Follow the signal bearing — it could lead us home",
  "event_subspaceEcho_choice0_outcome": "The heading adjustment is slight. Whether the voices are real or not, the crew sails with purpose.",
  "event_subspaceEcho_choice1_text": "Record everything for analysis",
  "event_subspaceEcho_choice1_outcome": "Linguists and physicists pore over the recording. They extract navigational references that improve our charts.",
  "event_subspaceEcho_choice2_text": "Dismiss it — space plays tricks on the lonely",
  "event_subspaceEcho_choice2_outcome": "The pragmatic choice. Some crew are disappointed, but the ship stays on its proven course.",
  "event_boonPerfectCalm_title": "The Great Calm",
  "event_boonPerfectCalm_narrative": "For reasons no physicist can explain, the ship enters a region of space that is preternaturally still — no radiation, no micro-debris, no gravitational interference. Every system on the ship runs at peak efficiency. The crew sleeps soundly for the first time in months.",
  "event_boonPerfectCalm_choice0_text": "Use the calm for comprehensive repairs",
  "event_boonPerfectCalm_choice0_outcome": "Repair crews work in perfect conditions. Every system gets attention. The ship emerges renewed.",
  "event_boonPerfectCalm_choice1_text": "Let the crew rest — they've earned it",
  "event_boonPerfectCalm_choice1_outcome": "A ship-wide stand-down. Colonists sleep, share meals, tell stories. The human cost of the voyage is, briefly, repaid.",
  "event_boonAncientWaystation_title": "Ancient Waystation",
  "event_boonAncientWaystation_narrative": "Nestled in the gravity well between two dead stars, an ancient station still functions — automated, patient, waiting for travellers. Its bays open as we approach. Repair drones activate. Fuel reserves extend toward us. Someone, long ago, built this for people like us.",
  "event_boonAncientWaystation_choice0_text": "Dock and accept everything it offers",
  "event_boonAncientWaystation_choice0_outcome": "The station repairs, refuels, and recalibrates the ship with technology centuries ahead of ours. When we depart, the station powers down — its purpose fulfilled.",
  "event_boonAncientWaystation_choice1_text": "Accept repairs but leave it running for others who follow",
  "event_boonAncientWaystation_choice1_outcome": "We take only what we need and transmit the station's coordinates back toward Earth. The crew feels noble.",
  "event_relicSentinel_title": "The Sentinel",
  "event_relicSentinel_narrative": "A towering construct orbits a barren moon — a lone guardian left behind by its builders. It is easily a kilometre tall, shaped like a spear of black glass. As we approach, a single red eye opens at its apex and tracks the ship. It does not fire. It does not hail. It watches.",
  "event_relicSentinel_choice0_text": "Transmit our mission profile — show we mean no harm",
  "event_relicSentinel_choice0_outcome": "The eye dims to amber, then green. A data packet arrives: coordinates of three star systems marked \"SAFE\" in a universal mathematical notation. A gift from a watchman.",
  "event_relicSentinel_choice1_text": "Hold position and study it passively",
  "event_relicSentinel_choice1_outcome": "Hours of observation yield insights into materials science that shouldn't be possible. The hull plating team takes frantic notes.",
  "event_relicSentinel_choice2_text": "Withdraw immediately — we don't know its rules",
  "event_relicSentinel_choice2_outcome": "The eye closes as we retreat. Whatever test that was, we chose not to take it. The crew debates for days.",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_title": "Wandering Seed",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_narrative": "A small, elegant probe tumbles through the void, broadcasting on every frequency simultaneously. Its shell is ceramic, etched with symbols that shift when observed. Inside: a pressurised chamber containing soil, seeds, and frozen microorganisms from a world that no longer exists.",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_choice0_text": "Integrate the biological payload into our seed banks",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_choice0_outcome": "Alien seeds and microbes are carefully catalogued and preserved. They could terraform a barren world into something alive. Biologists call it a miracle in a bottle.",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_choice1_text": "Study the probe's propulsion and navigation systems",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_choice1_outcome": "The probe's drive is centuries beyond ours — a reactionless thruster the size of a fist. Engineers reverse-engineer fragments of the design.",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_choice2_text": "Preserve the entire probe intact as a cultural artefact",
  "event_relicSeedProbe_choice2_outcome": "Displayed in the ship's atrium, the alien seed becomes a symbol of kinship between species. Someone else, somewhere, tried to save their world too.",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_title": "Warning Buoy",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_narrative": "A network of small buoys, hundreds of them, arranged in a perfect geometric pattern across our flight path. Each emits the same signal — a simple repeating pulse that increases in frequency the closer we get. It feels like a warning. Or a fence.",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_choice0_text": "Heed the warning — alter course around the network",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_choice0_outcome": "The detour costs time and stresses navigation, but as we skirt the boundary, long-range sensors detect what lies beyond: a region of space littered with the debris of shattered worlds. The buoys saved us.",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_choice1_text": "Push through — we can't afford detours",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_choice1_outcome": "Nothing happens as we cross the line. The buoys go silent. Whatever they were guarding against, it's either gone or we got lucky. The crew breathes again.",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_choice2_text": "Capture a buoy for analysis",
  "event_relicWarningBuoy_choice2_outcome": "The buoy's innards contain a compressed data archive — stellar cartography of this region from a million years ago. Some of the data is still accurate.",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_title": "The Mirror Array",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_narrative": "Thousands of flat, reflective surfaces hang motionless in space, arranged in concentric rings spanning hundreds of kilometres. They focus starlight from a distant sun into a single point — an artificial star, burning in the void. Someone built a lighthouse between galaxies.",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_choice0_text": "Bask in the focused light — recharge everything",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_choice0_outcome": "The concentrated starlight floods our solar collectors. Power reserves surge. The warm light lifts every soul aboard after months in cold dark.",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_choice1_text": "Study the mirror material — it shouldn't exist",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_choice1_outcome": "The mirrors are made of a material with perfect reflectivity — zero absorption at any wavelength. Engineers extract a shard. Hull plating will never be the same.",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_choice2_text": "Search the focal point — something is being illuminated",
  "event_relicMirrorArray_choice2_outcome": "At the convergence point: a small capsule, perfectly preserved in concentrated light. Inside, a holographic star map so detailed it takes our computers days to index.",
  "event_relicGraveyard_title": "The Probe Graveyard",
  "event_relicGraveyard_narrative": "We drift into a cloud of derelict probes — thousands of them, from dozens of different civilisations. Some are ancient beyond reckoning, fused by cosmic radiation into metallic fossils. Others still blink with fading power. This was a crossroads once. Every species that passed this way left something behind.",
  "event_relicGraveyard_choice0_text": "Systematic salvage — harvest the best technology",
  "event_relicGraveyard_choice0_outcome": "Engineering teams work in shifts, stripping alien tech from a hundred different designs. The fusion of ideas produces breakthroughs in every system.",
  "event_relicGraveyard_choice1_text": "Focus on the navigation data stored in their memory banks",
  "event_relicGraveyard_choice1_outcome": "Cross-referencing star charts from a dozen species creates the most complete map of this galactic arm ever assembled.",
  "event_relicGraveyard_choice2_text": "Add our own probe to the graveyard — leave a marker",
  "event_relicGraveyard_choice2_outcome": "We fabricate a small beacon carrying humanity's story and add it to the collection. The crew feels connected to something vast and ancient.",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_title": "The Dreamcatcher",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_narrative": "A web of filaments, thin as spider silk but spanning thousands of kilometres, is strung between two rogue planetoids. It is not a net — it's an antenna, tuned to frequencies that correspond to human brainwave patterns. When we enter its range, every sleeping colonist begins to dream the same dream: a thriving city under an amber sky.",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_choice0_text": "Record the dream coordinates — the city may be real",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_choice0_outcome": "Neuroscientists decode spatial information from the shared dream. It corresponds to a real star system — and the city in the vision wasn't a metaphor. Someone is out there, and they're expecting us.",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_choice1_text": "Harvest filament samples — the material is extraordinary",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_choice1_outcome": "The filaments are a room-temperature superconductor. Integrated into our systems, they reduce power loss to nearly zero.",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_choice2_text": "Cut the web and free the dreamers",
  "event_relicDreamcatcher_choice2_outcome": "The dreams stop. Colonists wake disoriented but unharmed. Some mourn the lost vision. Others are grateful to sleep without alien whispers.",
  "event_relicRosetta_title": "Rosetta Object",
  "event_relicRosetta_narrative": "A small, dense cube of unknown metal tumbles past the ship. Each face is inscribed with the same message in a different notation system — mathematical, chemical, genetic, acoustic, electromagnetic, and one we cannot identify. It is a Rosetta Stone for the cosmos.",
  "event_relicRosetta_choice0_text": "Decode the sixth face — the unknown notation",
  "event_relicRosetta_choice0_outcome": "Months of analysis yield a breakthrough: the sixth system encodes spatial coordinates using gravity waves. Our understanding of physics takes a generational leap.",
  "event_relicRosetta_choice1_text": "Use the chemical face to synthesise new compounds",
  "event_relicRosetta_choice1_outcome": "The chemical notation describes materials we've never imagined. Engineers fabricate hull patches that are lighter and stronger than anything from Earth.",
  "event_relicRosetta_choice2_text": "Broadcast the genetic face to our seed banks",
  "event_relicRosetta_choice2_outcome": "The genetic notation contains optimised DNA sequences for radiation resistance and nutrient absorption. Our crops and colonists will be hardier on alien soil.",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_title": "Ghost Fleet",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_narrative": "Scanners paint a chilling picture: a fleet of alien warships, hundreds strong, hanging motionless in formation. They are ancient — power readings are zero, hulls pitted by aeons of micro-impacts. Whatever battle they were sailing toward never came. They've been waiting here, dead and patient, for longer than human civilisation has existed.",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_choice0_text": "Board the flagship — if anyone had the best tech, it did",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_choice0_outcome": "The flagship's command deck still holds an intact tactical computer. Its predictive algorithms are centuries ahead of ours. Navigation and threat detection improve dramatically.",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_choice1_text": "Strip armour plating from the escort vessels",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_choice1_outcome": "Alien warship armour is designed to withstand weapons we can't even conceptualise. Bolted onto our hull, it makes the colony ship nearly indestructible.",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_choice2_text": "Salvage their cryogenic systems — they carried soldiers",
  "event_relicGhostFleet_choice2_outcome": "Alien cryo-tech operates on principles we've never considered. Our pods run cooler, smoother, and more reliably after the retrofit.",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_title": "Scanner Calibration Drift",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_narrative": "Routine diagnostics reveal that several scanner subsystems have drifted out of calibration after the last FTL jump. The atmospheric and temperature scanners are reading ghost signals. Engineers can fix them, but it will take time and resources.",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_choice0_text": "Full recalibration — divert tech resources",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_choice0_outcome": "A painstaking realignment restores both scanners to near-perfect accuracy, but the tech bay is drained.",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_choice1_text": "Quick fix — recalibrate atmospheric only",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_choice1_outcome": "The atmospheric scanner is restored. The temperature scanner remains unreliable for now.",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_choice2_text": "Deploy a probe for reference calibration",
  "event_scannerCalibrationDrift_choice2_outcome": "The probe provides a clean reference signal. Both scanners lock on and recalibrate automatically.",
  "event_ionStormScanners_title": "Ion Storm Interference",
  "event_ionStormScanners_narrative": "An ion storm sweeps through the sector, flooding scanner arrays with noise. The mineral and water detection systems are taking the brunt of the electromagnetic interference.",
  "event_ionStormScanners_choice0_text": "Power down scanners until the storm passes",
  "event_ionStormScanners_choice0_outcome": "The scanners survive but lose calibration data. Mineral and water readings will be less precise.",
  "event_ionStormScanners_choice1_text": "Keep scanning — push through the noise",
  "event_ionStormScanners_choice1_outcome": "Raw data floods in, but the filter circuits burn out on two subsystems. Gravimetric scans are also affected.",
  "event_ionStormScanners_choice2_text": "Use the storm to stress-test and improve filters",
  "event_ionStormScanners_choice2_outcome": "The science team uses the noise to train adaptive filters. Water scanner improves, but mineral scanner takes damage.",
  "event_bioScannerContamination_title": "Bio-Scanner Contamination",
  "event_bioScannerContamination_narrative": "The life-signs scanner has been contaminated by residual organic matter from the last planetary scan. False positives are everywhere. The gravimetric scanner is also showing sympathetic noise.",
  "event_bioScannerContamination_choice0_text": "Sterilise the sensor array — full decontamination",
  "event_bioScannerContamination_choice0_outcome": "A thorough cleaning restores the life-signs scanner but the chemical agents corrode the gravimetric sensor housing.",
  "event_bioScannerContamination_choice1_text": "Software filter — compensate algorithmically",
  "event_bioScannerContamination_choice1_outcome": "The filter works well enough, but underlying contamination will slowly degrade both systems.",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_title": "Scanner Power Surge",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_narrative": "A power conduit near the scanner bay overloads, sending a surge through multiple subsystems. The atmospheric and life-signs scanners take direct hits. Shields absorb some of the excess.",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_choice0_text": "Reroute power — save the scanners",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_choice0_outcome": "Quick action by the engineering team limits the damage, but the shields take the redirected energy.",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_choice1_text": "Let the surge run its course",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_choice1_outcome": "Scanners take the full brunt. Atmospheric and life-signs readings are significantly degraded.",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_choice2_text": "Sacrifice a probe's power cell to absorb the surge",
  "event_scannerPowerSurge_choice2_outcome": "The probe's capacitors soak up the excess energy like a sponge. Scanner damage is negligible.",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_title": "The World Engine",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_narrative": "Deep sensor sweeps reveal something impossible: a machine the size of a small moon, dormant in the dark between stars. Its surface is covered in continent-scale mechanisms — atmosphere processors, magnetic field generators, tectonic stabilisers. Someone built a machine that builds worlds.",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_choice0_text": "Download the terraforming blueprints",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_choice0_outcome": "The blueprints are vast and partially corrupted, but what we recover could make any hostile world habitable. Our colonists will reshape their new home.",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_choice1_text": "Harvest construction materials from its hull",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_choice1_outcome": "The World Engine's hull is made of metamaterials that self-repair when damaged. Integrated into our ship, they slowly mend existing hull breaches.",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_choice2_text": "Attempt to reactivate it — aim it at our target system",
  "event_relicWorldEngine_choice2_outcome": "The machine stirs. Ancient systems cycle through startup sequences. A beam of energy lances toward a distant star. Whether it works won't be known until we arrive, but the readings are promising.",
  "event_uneventfulMaintenance_title": "Routine Maintenance Shift",
  "event_uneventfulMaintenance_narrative": "Nothing demands attention. The ship hums steadily through the void and the duty roster calls for a routine maintenance window. The crew chief asks where to focus the shift's effort.",
  "event_uneventfulMaintenance_choice0_text": "Focus on hull micro-fracture sealing",
  "event_uneventfulMaintenance_choice0_outcome": "A quiet shift spent patching hairline cracks. Nothing dramatic, but the hull is marginally better for it.",
  "event_uneventfulMaintenance_choice1_text": "Recalibrate the forward scanners",
  "event_uneventfulMaintenance_choice1_outcome": "The scanner technician spends a few hours fine-tuning. The readings sharpen ever so slightly.",
  "event_uneventfulQuietWatch_title": "Quiet Watch",
  "event_uneventfulQuietWatch_narrative": "The stars drift by in silence. The bridge is calm, the instruments steady. It is one of those rare stretches where the universe asks nothing of you.",
  "event_uneventfulQuietWatch_choice0_text": "Let the crew rest — they've earned a quiet shift",
  "event_uneventfulQuietWatch_choice0_outcome": "A few hours of genuine peace. People sleep deeper, tensions ease, and the cultural officer notes a slight lift in morale.",
  "event_uneventfulQuietWatch_choice1_text": "Run low-priority diagnostics while it's calm",
  "event_uneventfulQuietWatch_choice1_outcome": "Minor issues are caught and logged. Nothing urgent, but the tech logs are a little cleaner.",
  "event_uneventfulCryopodCheck_title": "Cryopod Check — All Nominal",
  "event_uneventfulCryopodCheck_narrative": "The quarterly cryopod audit comes and goes without a single alarm. Every pod reads green. The medical team has a rare moment of calm.",
  "event_uneventfulCryopodCheck_choice0_text": "Wake a few colonists briefly for a morale visit",
  "event_uneventfulCryopodCheck_choice0_outcome": "Three colonists are brought to consciousness for an hour. They share stories, hug old friends, and return to cryo smiling.",
  "event_uneventfulCryopodCheck_choice1_text": "Let them sleep — don't risk unnecessary wake cycles",
  "event_uneventfulCryopodCheck_choice1_outcome": "The pods continue their flawless operation. The medics enjoy a quiet cup of tea instead.",
  "event_uneventfulCartography_title": "Stellar Cartography Update",
  "event_uneventfulCartography_narrative": "The navigation team's scheduled cartography update reveals nothing unusual — just the expected star fields shifting as we travel. A calm day for the navigators.",
  "event_uneventfulCartography_choice0_text": "Recalibrate navigation against the new star positions",
  "event_uneventfulCartography_choice0_outcome": "A small heading correction, barely perceptible. The nav computer hums contentedly.",
  "event_uneventfulCartography_choice1_text": "Update the star charts for the colony archive",
  "event_uneventfulCartography_choice1_outcome": "Future colonists will have slightly better maps of this region. A small gift to posterity.",
  "event_uneventfulAnniversary_title": "Ship's Anniversary",
  "event_uneventfulAnniversary_narrative": "One year since launch — or is it two? Time blurs in deep space. Someone in the galley has baked a cake from reconstituted stores. The captain must decide how to mark the occasion.",
  "event_uneventfulAnniversary_choice0_text": "Small celebration — music, cake, a toast to Earth",
  "event_uneventfulAnniversary_choice0_outcome": "An hour of warmth in the cold void. People laugh, some cry, and everyone feels a little more human.",
  "event_uneventfulAnniversary_choice1_text": "Business as usual — we celebrate when we arrive",
  "event_uneventfulAnniversary_choice1_outcome": "The crew respects the stoic approach. Focus sharpens, and the on-duty team runs an extra systems check.",
  "event_databaseLiterature_title": "Earth's Literature Archives",
  "event_databaseLiterature_narrative": "The ship's AI opens a long-sealed section of the cultural database: the complete literature archive of Earth. Novels, poetry, plays — millions of works spanning every language and era. The crew gathers for a reading.",
  "event_databaseLiterature_choice0_text": "Broadcast selected readings ship-wide",
  "event_databaseLiterature_choice0_outcome": "Shakespeare echoes through the corridors. Rumi's verses play in the hydroponics bay. The crew remembers what they carry.",
  "event_databaseLiterature_choice1_text": "Index the archive for educational programs",
  "event_databaseLiterature_choice1_outcome": "The cataloguing effort strengthens the ship's knowledge base and gives the cultural officer new teaching materials.",
  "event_databaseSchematics_title": "Engineering Schematic Review",
  "event_databaseSchematics_narrative": "An engineer stumbles upon a forgotten partition in the ship's database: detailed schematics from Earth's final decade of engineering — fusion reactor designs, metamaterial blueprints, and experimental propulsion concepts.",
  "event_databaseSchematics_choice0_text": "Prioritise the propulsion concepts for the tech team",
  "event_databaseSchematics_choice0_outcome": "The schematics reveal efficiency improvements the original builders never had time to implement. The tech bay buzzes.",
  "event_databaseSchematics_choice1_text": "Share the knowledge broadly — every department benefits",
  "event_databaseSchematics_choice1_outcome": "Hull engineers, scanner techs, and medics all find useful insights. A rising tide lifts every system, slightly.",
  "event_databaseCorruption_title": "Cultural Preservation Scan",
  "event_databaseCorruption_narrative": "A scheduled integrity check of the cultural database reveals bit rot — sections of music, oral histories, and religious texts have degraded beyond recovery. Not everything survived the journey.",
  "event_databaseCorruption_choice0_text": "Divert tech resources to salvage what remains",
  "event_databaseCorruption_choice0_outcome": "Engineers halt other work to run data recovery algorithms. They save most of it, but the effort costs the tech bay.",
  "event_databaseCorruption_choice1_text": "Ask colonists to recreate the lost works from memory",
  "event_databaseCorruption_choice1_outcome": "A beautiful, imperfect effort. What is rebuilt belongs to the voyage, not to Earth. A new tradition is born.",
  "event_databaseBreakthrough_title": "Archived Research Breakthrough",
  "event_databaseBreakthrough_narrative": "A physicist cross-referencing old Earth research papers in the database discovers that two unrelated studies, combined, describe a new method for long-range spectral analysis. The implications are enormous.",
  "event_databaseBreakthrough_choice0_text": "Implement the new analysis method in the scanner array",
  "event_databaseBreakthrough_choice0_outcome": "The scanner team works feverishly. Within days, spectral resolution doubles. Distant planets reveal their secrets.",
  "event_databaseBreakthrough_choice1_text": "Publish the finding ship-wide — inspire more research",
  "event_databaseBreakthrough_choice1_outcome": "The breakthrough sparks a wave of cross-disciplinary study. Tech improves broadly, and the crew feels intellectually alive.",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_title": "Alien Fleet on the Horizon",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_narrative": "Long-range scanners paint a terrifying picture: a fleet of alien vessels, numbering in the hundreds, moving in perfect formation across the starfield. They dwarf our ship. Their heading will bring them within sensor range in hours. First contact — on their terms or ours.",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_choice0_text": "Observe silently — go dark and watch",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_choice0_outcome": "The ship powers down to minimal emissions. The fleet passes like a school of luminous whales, unaware of the tiny human vessel hiding in their wake. Scanner data is extraordinary.",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_choice1_text": "Attempt first contact — transmit a greeting",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_choice1_outcome": "A single vessel breaks formation and approaches. A burst of data arrives — star charts, warnings, and something that might be music. Then it rejoins the fleet and they are gone.",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_choice2_text": "Flee — alter course immediately",
  "event_alienFleetSighting_choice2_outcome": "The ship burns hard in the opposite direction. The course change is expensive and stressful, but the fleet never notices us. Safety at a cost.",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_title": "Alien Trade Offer",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_narrative": "An alien vessel, smaller than ours but radiating immense power, matches our speed and broadcasts a simple repeating message. Our linguists decode it within hours: it is an offer to trade. Three categories of exchange are proposed.",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_choice0_text": "Trade technical schematics for alien star charts",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_choice0_outcome": "We transmit our propulsion designs; they respond with navigational data covering a vast swath of unexplored space. Our charts improve dramatically, though we've shared our technology with an unknown species.",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_choice1_text": "Trade cultural data for ship repairs",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_choice1_outcome": "We beam our music, art, and history. In return, alien repair drones swarm the hull, sealing breaches with materials we cannot identify. The hull gleams. Our soul is shared.",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_choice2_text": "Refuse the trade — the risk is too great",
  "event_alienTradeOffer_choice2_outcome": "The alien vessel waits for a time, then departs without incident. The crew is relieved but wonders what was lost.",
  "event_alienWarning_title": "Alien Warning Broadcast",
  "event_alienWarning_narrative": "Every speaker on the ship crackles to life with an alien voice — translated by our AI in real-time: \"DANGER AHEAD. TURN BACK. THE DARKNESS CONSUMES.\" The broadcast repeats, then dies. Long-range sensors show an anomalous void on our current heading.",
  "event_alienWarning_choice0_text": "Heed the warning — alter course around the void",
  "event_alienWarning_choice0_outcome": "The detour adds significant strain to navigation, but as we skirt the void's edge, sensors confirm: nothing that entered that region ever came out. We owe a debt to unknown voices.",
  "event_alienWarning_choice1_text": "Ignore the warning — stay on course",
  "event_alienWarning_choice1_outcome": "We push through. The void turns out to be a region of intense micro-debris. Hull and scanners take punishment before we clear the far side.",
  "event_alienWarning_choice2_text": "Investigate the void's edge with a probe",
  "event_alienWarning_choice2_outcome": "The probe enters the void and transmits extraordinary data before going silent. The scanner team extracts valuable readings, but the probe is lost.",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_title": "Transmissions from the Target World",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_narrative": "The communications array picks up structured electromagnetic signals originating from our target planet. They are unmistakable: regular, modulated, artificial. Someone is already there. The colony's entire premise shifts in an instant.",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_choice0_text": "Transmit a peaceful greeting — announce our arrival",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_choice0_outcome": "A brave choice. The signal changes pattern after our broadcast — they heard us. Whether this is welcome or warning is unclear, but the door is open.",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_choice1_text": "Listen only — learn before revealing ourselves",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_choice1_outcome": "Months of passive listening build a picture of the native civilisation. They are cautious, territorial, but not hostile. We arrive informed.",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_choice2_text": "Jam the signal — deny them knowledge of our approach",
  "event_nativeSignalDetected_choice2_outcome": "The jamming works, but it is an act of aggression against a people we haven't met. The crew is divided on the morality.",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_title": "Alien Probe Intercept",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_narrative": "A small, elegant probe — not of human origin — matches our velocity and begins scanning the ship. Its design language matches the signals from the target planet. The natives sent a welcome committee. Or a surveillance drone.",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_choice0_text": "Allow the scan — show we have nothing to hide",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_choice0_outcome": "The probe completes its survey and transmits a data burst back toward the planet. Minutes later, a second burst arrives for us: atmospheric data, safe landing zones, and what might be an invitation.",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_choice1_text": "Capture the probe for study",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_choice1_outcome": "The probe is tractored into the cargo bay. Its technology is fascinating but the act of capture may be seen as hostile by its makers.",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_choice2_text": "Destroy it — we don't know its intent",
  "event_nativeProbeEncounter_choice2_outcome": "A single pulse reduces the probe to fragments. The crew feels safer, but a potential bridge has been burned.",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_title": "First Cultural Exchange",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_narrative": "A narrow-band data link has been established with the planetary natives. They send us images, sounds, and mathematical sequences. Our linguists and cultural officers work around the clock to prepare a response. This is the most important conversation in human history.",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_choice0_text": "Share Earth's art and music — lead with beauty",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_choice0_outcome": "We transmit Bach, Aboriginal dot paintings, and the sound of rain on leaves. The response is a cascade of alien harmonics that makes the crew weep. Understanding deepens.",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_choice1_text": "Share scientific knowledge — lead with reason",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_choice1_outcome": "We transmit our periodic table, star charts, and physics. They respond with corrections and additions. Our tech leaps forward, but the exchange feels transactional.",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_choice2_text": "Send a probe with physical samples — DNA, seeds, water",
  "event_nativeCulturalExchange_choice2_outcome": "A probe carries the essence of Earth to alien hands. The natives respond with a similar gift — biological samples from their world. Biologists are ecstatic.",
  "event_landingThrusterMalfunction_title": "Landing Thruster Malfunction",
  "event_landingThrusterMalfunction_narrative": "During a routine systems check, the landing thrusters misfire — a sharp bang echoes through the lower decks and the ship lurches. Diagnostics reveal a cracked fuel injector in the primary landing array. Without repair, planetfall will be rough.",
  "event_landingThrusterMalfunction_choice0_text": "Divert the tech team to fabricate a replacement injector",
  "event_landingThrusterMalfunction_choice0_outcome": "Engineers work double shifts and machine a new injector from spare hull alloy. The landing system is restored, though the tech bay is depleted.",
  "event_landingThrusterMalfunction_choice1_text": "Deploy a probe to test thruster calibration in vacuum",
  "event_landingThrusterMalfunction_choice1_outcome": "The probe provides real-time thrust data that lets engineers recalibrate around the damaged injector. Not a full fix, but the landing system stabilises.",
  "event_landingSimDrill_title": "Landing Simulation Drill",
  "event_landingSimDrill_narrative": "With planetfall growing closer, the captain orders a full landing simulation. The crew straps in, systems are tested under load, and the virtual descent begins. It is the most realistic rehearsal they will get.",
  "event_landingSimDrill_choice0_text": "Focus on technical precision — run the drill by the book",
  "event_landingSimDrill_choice0_outcome": "The simulation reveals two minor calibration errors that are immediately corrected. The landing system is tighter for it.",
  "event_landingSimDrill_choice1_text": "Make it a ship-wide event — broadcast the simulation",
  "event_landingSimDrill_choice1_outcome": "Colonists watch from every screen aboard. The shared experience of the simulated descent — the shaking, the cheering — bonds the crew like nothing else.",
  "event_dysonSphere_title": "The Dyson Sphere",
  "event_dysonSphere_narrative": "Sensors detect an impossible structure — a partial Dyson sphere surrounding a distant star, harvesting its entire energy output. Whoever built this transcended anything humanity has ever conceived. A docking port appears to open as we approach.",
  "event_dysonSphere_choice0_text": "Dock and explore the structure",
  "event_dysonSphere_choice0_outcome": "Inside, automated systems gift us technology that leaps our capabilities forward by centuries. Five engineers are lost to the station's defense mechanisms before it recognises our intent. The constructors are rebuilt with alien alloys.",
  "event_dysonSphere_choice1_text": "Harvest energy from the exterior",
  "event_dysonSphere_choice1_outcome": "We bathe in the sphere's radiant overflow. Every system aboard charges to maximum. The crew watches in stunned silence.",
  "event_dysonSphere_choice2_text": "Study from a safe distance and move on",
  "event_dysonSphere_choice2_outcome": "Long-range scans reveal construction principles that revolutionize our understanding of engineering.",
  "event_nanotechPlague_title": "The Nanotech Plague",
  "event_nanotechPlague_narrative": "A cloud of rogue nanomachines, remnants of some dead civilization's weapons program, infiltrates the ship through hull micro-fractures. They are disassembling non-critical systems at the molecular level. The swarm is spreading fast.",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice0_text": "EMP burst — fry everything in the affected sections",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice0_outcome": "The electromagnetic pulse destroys the nanites but also damages our own electronics in those sections. Colonists in the blast zone suffer burns.",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice1_text": "Vent the affected sections to vacuum",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice1_outcome": "Without atmosphere, the nanites slow and die. But the sections are lost, along with stored supplies and culture archives.",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice2_text": "Reprogram them — turn weapons into tools",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice2_outcome": "A brilliant engineer cracks the nanite code, but five crew members in the most affected sections are already beyond saving. The reprogrammed swarm begins repairing the ship instead of destroying it.",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice3_text": "Sacrifice a probe's AI core to create a counter-swarm",
  "event_nanotechPlague_choice3_outcome": "The probe's processors are repurposed to control a defensive nanite swarm. The plague is neutralized with minimal losses.",
  "event_prematureAwakening_title": "The Premature Awakening",
  "event_prematureAwakening_narrative": "A cascade failure in the cryopod bay wakes 200 colonists decades early. They are confused, frightened, and consuming resources meant for the landing phase. Among them are children who have never known anything but the ship.",
  "event_prematureAwakening_choice0_text": "Integrate them into the crew — more hands, more hope",
  "event_prematureAwakening_choice0_outcome": "The awakened colonists become productive crew members. Twenty colonists don't survive the abrupt thaw, but the rest rally. Resources stretch thin but spirits soar.",
  "event_prematureAwakening_choice1_text": "Attempt to re-freeze them — risky but necessary",
  "event_prematureAwakening_choice1_outcome": "The re-freezing process is imperfect. Most survive, but some are lost. The survivors carry psychological scars.",
  "event_prematureAwakening_choice2_text": "Give them their own section of the ship",
  "event_prematureAwakening_choice2_outcome": "Ten colonists are lost to complications from the emergency thaw, but the rest form a micro-colony within the ship. They develop their own culture and governance, a rehearsal for planetary settlement.",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_title": "The Hidden Passengers",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_narrative": "Deep in the cargo hold, behind false bulkheads, security discovers an entire hidden community — 80 people who boarded illegally before launch. They have been living in the walls of the ship for the entire voyage, maintaining their own gardens and power taps.",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_choice0_text": "Welcome them — 80 more colonists is a gift",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_choice0_outcome": "The hidden community brings skills in improvised engineering and resourcefulness that stun the crew. Their gardens are transplanted to the main biodome.",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_choice1_text": "Confine them and redistribute their stolen resources",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_choice1_outcome": "The recovered supplies boost several systems, but the confinement of families — including children — haunts the crew.",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_choice2_text": "Negotiate — they join us as equals if they share their tech",
  "event_stowawaysAdvanced_choice2_outcome": "Their improvised power cells and hydroponic tricks improve ship efficiency. A tense but productive integration begins.",
  "event_alienReservation_title": "The Alien Reservation",
  "event_alienReservation_narrative": "We stumble upon an alien nature preserve — a region of space deliberately seeded with habitable planets and protected by automated sentinels. The guardians scan us and project a message: \"You may settle ONE world. Choose wisely. Interfere with the others and you will be removed.\"",
  "event_alienReservation_choice0_text": "Accept gratefully — one world is all we need",
  "event_alienReservation_choice0_outcome": "The sentinels guide us to a prepared world. Scans reveal it is extraordinarily suitable for human life.",
  "event_alienReservation_choice1_text": "Negotiate for better terms — humanity needs room to grow",
  "event_alienReservation_choice1_outcome": "The sentinels consider our plea. They upgrade our scanners with data on dozens of systems beyond the preserve.",
  "event_alienReservation_choice2_text": "Decline and leave — we won't be caged",
  "event_alienReservation_choice2_outcome": "The crew debates for days. Freedom over safety. The sentinels allow our departure with a gift: a map of nearby hazards.",
  "event_cosmicHorror_title": "The Thing Between Stars",
  "event_cosmicHorror_narrative": "Something vast and dark occludes the stars ahead — not a nebula, not a black hole. It has no mass, no energy signature, no electromagnetic presence. But it is THERE, and it is aware of us. Crew members near the forward observation deck report overwhelming dread. Two have been sedated.",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice0_text": "Full reverse — get away NOW",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice0_outcome": "The ship strains against its own momentum. We escape, but the terror lingers. Some colonists never recover psychologically.",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice1_text": "Seal the observation deck and push through",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice1_outcome": "Three days of blind flight through the dark. When stars return, the crew weeps with relief. The hull is etched with patterns no one can explain.",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice2_text": "Attempt communication",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice2_outcome": "The entity responds — not in words, but in knowledge pressed directly into the minds of the crew. Star maps, physics, truths about the universe. Half the crew is enlightened. The other half is broken.",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice3_text": "Offer a probe as tribute",
  "event_cosmicHorror_choice3_outcome": "The probe drifts into the darkness and vanishes. The entity contracts slightly, as if satisfied. Our path clears.",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_title": "Glancing Meteor Strike",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_narrative": "A boulder-sized meteor clips the port side of the hull at a shallow angle. The impact tears away three metres of outer plating and sends shockwaves through the entire frame. Damage-control alarms scream across every deck.",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_choice0_text": "Divert all repair bots to the breach immediately",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_choice0_outcome": "The bots seal the worst of the damage, but the frantic draw on tech reserves leaves secondary systems underserviced.",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_choice1_text": "Reduce thrust and let the crew patch it manually",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_choice1_outcome": "Slower progress, but the crew does solid work. Nav suffers from the reduced thrust window while we drift.",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_choice2_text": "Sacrifice a probe's hull plating as patch material",
  "event_meteorGlancingHit_choice2_outcome": "The probe is stripped for parts. The patch holds and hull integrity is preserved at the cost of one less scout.",
  "event_meteorDirectImpact_title": "Direct Meteor Impact",
  "event_meteorDirectImpact_narrative": "A half-tonne iron meteorite punches clean through the forward cargo bay at relative velocity exceeding 40 km/s. Two crew members in the adjacent corridor are unaccounted for. The bay is open to vacuum.",
  "event_meteorDirectImpact_choice0_text": "Seal cargo bay and search for survivors later",
  "event_meteorDirectImpact_choice0_outcome": "The bay is sealed in ninety seconds. Both crew members had already evacuated — barely. The hull takes permanent scarring.",
  "event_meteorDirectImpact_choice1_text": "Launch a full rescue operation before sealing",
  "event_meteorDirectImpact_choice1_outcome": "One survivor is pulled out. The extended exposure worsens the structural damage and drains tech reserves.",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_title": "Debris Field — Remnant Shower",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_narrative": "Long-range sensors failed to detect a dispersed field of meteor fragments until we were already inside it. Hundreds of fist-sized rocks are striking the hull at random intervals. Every hit is a lottery.",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_choice0_text": "Raise shields and push through at full speed",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_choice0_outcome": "The shields absorb most hits, but the sheer volume of impacts overwhelms them. Hull and shield systems both degrade.",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_choice1_text": "Cut engines and drift — minimise our profile",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_choice1_outcome": "A tense six hours of silence. Nav is thrown off by the unpowered drift, but the hull emerges with far fewer impacts.",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_choice2_text": "Deploy a probe as a forward shield",
  "event_meteorDebrisField_choice2_outcome": "The probe takes the brunt of the barrage. The ship slips through in its shadow with minor scratches.",
  "event_meteorShowerDense_title": "Unexpected Dense Meteor Shower",
  "event_meteorShowerDense_narrative": "A rogue comet disintegrated somewhere ahead of us, and we have flown straight into the heart of its trailing debris stream. The scanner arrays are being pelted with fragments and the landing system sensor housing has already taken a direct hit.",
  "event_meteorShowerDense_choice0_text": "Protect the landing system — rotate the ship",
  "event_meteorShowerDense_choice0_outcome": "The rotation shields the landing system but exposes the atmospheric scanner array to the brunt of the barrage.",
  "event_meteorShowerDense_choice1_text": "Shield the scanner arrays — they are irreplaceable",
  "event_meteorShowerDense_choice1_outcome": "The scanner banks survive mostly intact. The landing system takes moderate shrapnel damage we will have to live with.",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_title": "EMP Burst — Stellar Origin",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_narrative": "A compact stellar remnant we passed within a light-day of has discharged a focused electromagnetic pulse. Every unshielded circuit on the ship is at risk. We have seconds to decide what to protect.",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_choice0_text": "Route all surge protection to navigation and life support",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_choice0_outcome": "Navigation and life support survive intact. The scanner suite and tech bay absorb the pulse unshielded — both take heavy damage.",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_choice1_text": "Protect the scanner arrays and tech bay",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_choice1_outcome": "Science and engineering systems are preserved. Navigation misfires for hours afterward as its circuits slowly recover.",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_choice2_text": "Power down everything and restart post-pulse",
  "event_solarEmpBurst_choice2_outcome": "A cold restart is agonising — twelve hours of manual reboots. But no system is fried beyond recovery.",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_title": "Radiation Wave — Class 4 Exposure",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_narrative": "A solar radiation burst of unexpected intensity is sweeping through the ship's mid-decks. The cryopod bays are in the exposure path. Colonists in suspension have no natural protection against hard radiation at this dosage level.",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_choice0_text": "Flood the cryopod bays with coolant as radiation shielding",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_choice0_outcome": "The coolant absorbs most of the radiation. The cryopods survive, but the coolant system itself is partially degraded. Fifteen in the worst-affected pods don't make it.",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_choice1_text": "Vent outer deck atmosphere to create a vacuum buffer",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_choice1_outcome": "The vacuum layer reduces penetrating radiation significantly. Twenty colonists in pods nearest the vented sections suffer lethal exposure. Hull stress from the pressure differential is unavoidable.",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_choice2_text": "Reroute power to magnetic deflectors",
  "event_solarRadiationWave_choice2_outcome": "The deflectors cut radiation exposure by two-thirds. Eight colonists receive fatal doses through gaps in the deflector coverage. The power draw hammers the tech bay and leaves nav running on minimal power.",
  "event_coronalMassEjection_title": "Coronal Mass Ejection — Full Force",
  "event_coronalMassEjection_narrative": "A coronal mass ejection of unprecedented scale is overtaking us from behind. The plasma cloud will engulf the ship within the hour. Our shields were not designed for this class of event. No option is clean.",
  "event_coronalMassEjection_choice0_text": "Outrun it — push engines to one hundred twenty percent",
  "event_coronalMassEjection_choice0_outcome": "We gain enough distance to reduce exposure. The engines overheat and the nav computer flags structural overstress warnings across the board.",
  "event_coronalMassEjection_choice1_text": "Shelter behind a nearby planetoid's magnetic shadow",
  "event_coronalMassEjection_choice1_outcome": "The planetoid's field deflects most of the ejection. Navigating that close to an uncharted body scratches the hull and strains the landing system sensors.",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_title": "Cosmic Ray Burst — Scanner Interference",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_narrative": "A burst of ultra-high-energy cosmic rays has saturated all scanner electronics with noise. The mineralogical and gravimetric arrays are producing gibberish. Recalibration will take time we may not have.",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_choice0_text": "Full recalibration cycle — take the ship offline temporarily",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_choice0_outcome": "All scanners come back clean after four hours of careful recalibration. Nav suffers from the reduced situational awareness during the blackout window.",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_choice1_text": "Patch only the most critical arrays — leave the rest noisy",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_choice1_outcome": "Gravimetric and life-signs scanners are restored. The mineral and temperature arrays remain degraded indefinitely.",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_choice2_text": "Sacrifice probe telemetry hardware for replacement parts",
  "event_cosmicRayScannerInterference_choice2_outcome": "Cannibalising a probe's sensor package gives us the components to restore the scanner suite without a long recalibration.",
  "event_cosmicRayDnaDamage_title": "Cosmic Ray Burst — Colonist Exposure",
  "event_cosmicRayDnaDamage_narrative": "A secondary cosmic ray shower has penetrated the cryopod shielding in bay 6. Colonists in suspension are receiving cumulative DNA damage from ionising radiation. Without intervention, cell repair mechanisms will fail in the affected pods.",
  "event_cosmicRayDnaDamage_choice0_text": "Emergency thaw — bring affected colonists to consciousness",
  "event_cosmicRayDnaDamage_choice0_outcome": "Two hundred colonists are woken early. Forty with the most severe DNA damage don't respond to treatment. The medical team does what it can for the rest.",
  "event_cosmicRayDnaDamage_choice1_text": "Reroute hull armour plating to shield bay 6 — structural cost",
  "event_cosmicRayDnaDamage_choice1_outcome": "The colony is saved, but stripping armour from one section of the hull leaves the ship structurally vulnerable in that zone.",
  "event_coolantLeak_title": "Coolant Line Rupture",
  "event_coolantLeak_narrative": "A primary coolant line has ruptured behind the reactor wall. Superheated cryogenic fluid is spraying across a junction housing critical tech-bay conduits. The reactor temperature is climbing.",
  "event_coolantLeak_choice0_text": "Shut down the reactor and let it cool — accept full blackout",
  "event_coolantLeak_choice0_outcome": "A controlled shutdown prevents catastrophe. Twelve hours of life support on battery is harrowing, and systems restart imperfectly.",
  "event_coolantLeak_choice1_text": "Send a damage-control team in — risk crew exposure",
  "event_coolantLeak_choice1_outcome": "The team seals the rupture in forty minutes. One crew member is killed by superheated coolant exposure. The repair is solid.",
  "event_coolantLeak_choice2_text": "Divert coolant from cryopod bay as emergency supply",
  "event_coolantLeak_choice2_outcome": "The reactor is stabilised. The cryopod bay runs warmer than safe thresholds for six hours — minor but real cellular damage accumulates.",
  "event_powerGridFailure_title": "Main Power Grid Failure",
  "event_powerGridFailure_narrative": "A cascading fault has tripped the main power grid. Backup systems are holding life support and cryopod heating, but navigation, scanners, and the constructor bay are all dark. Every minute offline costs us course accuracy.",
  "event_powerGridFailure_choice0_text": "Restore nav and scanner first — accept extended constructor downtime",
  "event_powerGridFailure_choice0_outcome": "Navigation and scanner systems come back online in two hours. The constructor bay misses a critical maintenance cycle.",
  "event_powerGridFailure_choice1_text": "Restore constructors first — use them to speed the repair",
  "event_powerGridFailure_choice1_outcome": "The constructors reroute power efficiently. Full grid restoration happens faster, but nav drifts badly during the extended blackout.",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_title": "Life Support Cascade Glitch",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_narrative": "The life support management AI has entered an error loop, cycling carbon dioxide scrubbing intervals unpredictably. CO₂ levels across occupied decks are fluctuating. Crew are developing headaches; some are already incapacitated.",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_choice0_text": "Force a hard reset of the life support AI",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_choice0_outcome": "The reset clears the loop but leaves manual overrides running for ten hours. Three crew members succumb to CO₂ buildup before levels normalise.",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_choice1_text": "Patch the software loop — slower but safer",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_choice1_outcome": "The software team isolates and patches the fault over six tense hours. CO₂ levels slowly normalise. No hard reset needed.",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_choice2_text": "Evacuate affected decks and run on minimal life support",
  "event_lifeSupportGlitch_choice2_outcome": "Two colonists are lost in the confusion of the evacuation. Systems normalise after the AI is cold-restarted.",
  "event_waterRecyclerBreakdown_title": "Water Recycler Breakdown",
  "event_waterRecyclerBreakdown_narrative": "The primary water reclamation unit has seized. The backup unit is already running at capacity. Without intervention, the crew will be on emergency rations within forty-eight hours, and cryopod coolant feeds will be compromised within seventy-two.",
  "event_waterRecyclerBreakdown_choice0_text": "Pull every available tech hand to rebuild the reclaimer",
  "event_waterRecyclerBreakdown_choice0_outcome": "The unit is rebuilt in thirty hours. Four crew members, already weakened, don't survive the dehydration.",
  "event_waterRecyclerBreakdown_choice1_text": "Divert cryopod coolant reserves as emergency drinking supply",
  "event_waterRecyclerBreakdown_choice1_outcome": "The crew is sustained, but eight colonists in warming pods suffer irreversible cellular damage. The cryopod coolant margin shrinks dangerously.",
  "event_navComputerReboot_title": "Navigation Computer Emergency Reboot",
  "event_navComputerReboot_narrative": "The navigation computer has locked up mid-course-correction, leaving the ship in an uncontrolled slow spin. Every second of uncorrected rotation compounds our drift from the planned trajectory. A full reboot is the only fix.",
  "event_navComputerReboot_choice0_text": "Reboot immediately — accept the full blackout period",
  "event_navComputerReboot_choice0_outcome": "Four hours of blind flight while the system reloads. The spin is arrested, but the course error is significant.",
  "event_navComputerReboot_choice1_text": "Use manual thruster control to arrest the spin first",
  "event_navComputerReboot_choice1_outcome": "Skilled piloting stops the rotation before the reboot. Nav comes back with a smaller course error, but the manual burn stresses the hull.",
  "event_navComputerReboot_choice2_text": "Feed probe telemetry into the backup nav unit",
  "event_navComputerReboot_choice2_outcome": "The probe's inertial data gives the backup unit enough reference to hold course. The main nav reboots cleanly.",
  "event_crewAirlocked_title": "Crew Member at the Airlock",
  "event_crewAirlocked_narrative": "A colonist — awoken early for medical observation — has barricaded herself inside an external airlock and is cycling the outer door. She is not responding to communication. The psychological toll of deep space has broken something in her.",
  "event_crewAirlocked_choice0_text": "Override the airlock remotely — force it sealed",
  "event_crewAirlocked_choice0_outcome": "The door is locked before she can complete the cycle. She is sedated and returned to medical. The crew is shaken but united.",
  "event_crewAirlocked_choice1_text": "Send a counsellor in to talk her back",
  "event_crewAirlocked_choice1_outcome": "After three desperate hours, the counsellor brings her out alive. The incident sparks a broader mental health crisis on occupied decks.",
  "event_crewAirlocked_choice2_text": "Seal the corridor and let the incident resolve",
  "event_crewAirlocked_choice2_outcome": "The airlock cycles. The loss is recorded. The remaining crew members carry the weight of it for months.",
  "event_crewCryopodSabotage_title": "Cryopod Bay Sabotage",
  "event_crewCryopodSabotage_narrative": "Security feeds reveal a crew member — awoken three months ago for a routine rotation — methodically disabling cryopod heating elements in bay 4. When confronted, he screams that the colonists are parasites consuming resources that belong to the living crew.",
  "event_crewCryopodSabotage_choice0_text": "Arrest and isolate him immediately",
  "event_crewCryopodSabotage_choice0_outcome": "He is restrained. Forty pods were compromised before the alert. Emergency repair teams save most, but not all.",
  "event_crewCryopodSabotage_choice1_text": "Negotiate — hear his grievances before acting",
  "event_crewCryopodSabotage_choice1_outcome": "The negotiation reveals a deeper morale crisis. He stands down, but sixty pods have been tampered with by the time he does.",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_title": "Supply Hoarding Discovered",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_narrative": "Inventory audit reveals that a small group of crew members has been systematically diverting medical supplies, food rations, and spare tech components into a hidden cache. Their reasoning: they do not believe the mission will succeed, and they are preparing for the long way home.",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_choice0_text": "Confiscate everything and publicly reprimand the group",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_choice0_outcome": "The cache is recovered almost intact. Trust within the crew fractures badly. Productivity suffers for weeks.",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_choice1_text": "Quietly reassign them — do not make it a spectacle",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_choice1_outcome": "The situation is defused without panic. Some supplies are unrecoverable, and the underlying despair is never properly addressed.",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_choice2_text": "Put it to the crew — a democratic tribunal",
  "event_crewSupplyHoarder_choice2_outcome": "The tribunal process restores a sense of community justice. The morale hit from the scandal is offset by the collective decision-making.",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_title": "Mutiny — Engine Room Seized",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_narrative": "A faction of nineteen crew members has locked down the engine room and is demanding a vote to turn the ship around. They have disabled the emergency override panels. The rest of the crew watches on the monitors, waiting for command to act.",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_choice0_text": "Negotiate — grant them a genuine vote on the mission",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_choice0_outcome": "The vote is held. The mission continues by a narrow margin. The faction stands down, but the cultural wound runs deep.",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_choice1_text": "Cut power to the engine room and retake it by force",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_choice1_outcome": "Security retakes the room in four hours. Three injuries. The ringleaders are confined. Nav was in manual mode the entire time and drifted significantly.",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_choice2_text": "Flood the engine room with sleep gas from the ventilation system",
  "event_crewMutinyAttempt_choice2_outcome": "The gas disperses. The group wakes up in the brig with no injuries. The crew is disturbed by how quickly command weaponised life support.",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_title": "Hull Fatigue — Stress Fractures Detected",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_narrative": "Structural integrity scans reveal a network of micro-fractures spreading through the spine of the ship — cumulative damage from years of thermal cycling and micro-impacts. The fractures are not yet critical, but they are propagating.",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_choice0_text": "Emergency welding teams — work in shifts until it is sealed",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_choice0_outcome": "Weeks of exhausting repair work. The fractures are contained, but the tech bay is drained and morale sags from the relentless grind.",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_choice1_text": "Reduce thrust to lower structural stress — accept slower transit",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_choice1_outcome": "Lower thrust stops the fractures from propagating but does nothing to heal existing damage. Nav precision suffers from the altered thrust profile.",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_choice2_text": "Use constructor bots to lay composite reinforcement strips",
  "event_hullFatigueStress_choice2_outcome": "The constructors do excellent work. The spine is reinforced beyond its original specification. The constructor bay is exhausted but effective.",
  "event_hullPressureAnomaly_title": "Internal Pressure Anomaly",
  "event_hullPressureAnomaly_narrative": "Three mid-ship compartments are registering anomalous internal pressure differentials consistent with micro-scale structural deformation. If the walls are bowing inward, a catastrophic blowout could occur without further warning.",
  "event_hullPressureAnomaly_choice0_text": "Evacuate and seal the compartments immediately",
  "event_hullPressureAnomaly_choice0_outcome": "The compartments are sealed. Detailed inspection confirms wall deformation. The lost space disrupts operations and culture suffers from the cramped conditions.",
  "event_hullPressureAnomaly_choice1_text": "Vent the compartments to vacuum — halt pressure differential",
  "event_hullPressureAnomaly_choice1_outcome": "Venting arrests the deformation. The structural damage is limited, but three sections of the ship are permanently uninhabitable.",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_title": "Communication Array Failure",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_narrative": "The primary long-range communication array has gone silent. The last message from Earth was received eleven months ago, and now even the carrier signal is gone. Internal diagnostics suggest the dish alignment mechanism has seized in the cold.",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_choice0_text": "Send an EVA team to manually re-align the dish",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_choice0_outcome": "The EVA takes nine hours in open space. The dish is restored. One crew member suffers suit decompression during reentry — a close call that rattles everyone.",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_choice1_text": "Reroute through the science scanner array as a backup transmitter",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_choice1_outcome": "The science array is not optimised for communication. The signal is weak and unreliable, and the repurposing degrades scanner capability.",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_choice2_text": "Accept the silence — focus resources on the mission ahead",
  "event_commsArrayFailure_choice2_outcome": "The crew processes the loss of contact with Earth in different ways. For some it is liberating; for others, devastating.",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_title": "Fuel Line Rupture",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_narrative": "A crystalline fracture in fuel conduit 7-B is venting drive plasma into the maintenance shaft. The leak is small but accelerating. Uncontrolled, it will compromise both the nav drive efficiency and the structural integrity of the aft section.",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_choice0_text": "Isolate the conduit and run on reduced fuel capacity",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_choice0_outcome": "The conduit is shut down cleanly. We lose fifteen percent of drive efficiency permanently, which degrades nav precision for the remainder of the voyage.",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_choice1_text": "Attempt a hot repair — patch the conduit under live pressure",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_choice1_outcome": "The repair team succeeds, barely. The conduit holds, though imperfectly. Aft hull plating shows heat stress scoring.",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_choice2_text": "Drain the conduit using probe thruster tanks as overflow storage",
  "event_fuelLineRupture_choice2_outcome": "The probe is vented and used as a temporary fuel reservoir. The conduit is safely drained and repaired without pressure.",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_title": "Cryopod Temperature Cascade Warning",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_narrative": "Bay 2 cryopod temperatures are rising in a pattern consistent with a thermal runaway cascade. If the cascade reaches bay 3, it will trigger an automatic emergency thaw of over three hundred colonists. The ship cannot sustain that many conscious passengers simultaneously.",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_choice0_text": "Dump coolant reserves to arrest the cascade",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_choice0_outcome": "The coolant stops the cascade at the bay 2 border. Eighty colonists in bay 2 sustain suspension damage from the temperature spike.",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_choice1_text": "Controlled thaw of bay 2 before the cascade forces an uncontrolled one",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_choice1_outcome": "The controlled thaw is orderly but puts one hundred and forty colonists into an unprepared ship. Life support strains, culture deteriorates under crowding.",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_choice2_text": "Use constructor bots to physically isolate the bays with emergency bulkheads",
  "event_cryopodCascadeWarning_choice2_outcome": "The constructors erect thermal barriers in time. The cascade is stopped cold. The constructor bay is severely depleted by the emergency operation.",
  "event_cryopodSealDegradation_title": "Cryopod Seal Degradation — Systemic",
  "event_cryopodSealDegradation_narrative": "Routine checks reveal that a manufacturing batch of cryopod seals is degrading at three times the expected rate. The affected pods — numbering over four hundred — will begin losing atmospheric integrity within six months if not replaced.",
  "event_cryopodSealDegradation_choice0_text": "Manufacture replacement seals from raw material stocks",
  "event_cryopodSealDegradation_choice0_outcome": "The constructors produce replacement seals over eight weeks. Raw material reserves are drawn down sharply.",
  "event_cryopodSealDegradation_choice1_text": "Consolidate colonists — move them to pods with good seals",
  "event_cryopodSealDegradation_choice1_outcome": "Consolidation works but leaves some pods overcrowded. Cryogenic efficiency drops and long-term colonist health is compromised.",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_title": "Oxygen Scrubber Failure — Critical",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_narrative": "The primary oxygen scrubber bank has failed completely. CO₂ concentrations on inhabited decks are climbing toward dangerous levels. The backup scrubbers can handle roughly forty percent of the load. Every minute of inaction costs lives.",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_choice0_text": "Emergency hibernation — put the crew back under immediately",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_choice0_outcome": "The crew is rushed into temporary suspension. CO₂ levels stabilise with fewer active metabolisms. The scrubber is repaired by automated systems over the following week.",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_choice1_text": "Cannibalise components from the scanner array to rebuild the scrubber",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_choice1_outcome": "The scrubber is rebuilt in eleven tense hours. All crew survive, though some show signs of mild hypoxia. The scanner suite is permanently degraded.",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_choice2_text": "Vent the CO₂-rich atmosphere and replace from emergency oxygen tanks",
  "event_oxygenScrubberFailure_choice2_outcome": "The vent clears the atmosphere instantly. Emergency O₂ reserves are substantially depleted. If another failure occurs, there is no margin left.",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_title": "The Silent Voyager",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_narrative": "Long-range scanners pick up a drifting vessel — alien in design, dark, no power signatures. A boarding team finds a single occupant: a reptilian being strapped into the pilot's harness, long dead, clawed hands still clutching a crystalline device that pulses with faint light. The ship's log is intact but encrypted. Whatever killed this traveller, it wasn't violence — the expression frozen on its face is one of exhaustion, not fear. It died reaching for something it never found.",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice0_text": "Take the crystal device and study it",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice0_outcome": "The device interfaces with our tech systems in ways the engineers can barely comprehend. It appears to be a navigational computer of extraordinary sophistication. Star charts flood our displays — including data on planets we haven't reached yet.",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice1_text": "Decrypt the ship's log — learn what it knew",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice1_outcome": "Days of work yield a partial translation. The alien was a surveyor, cataloguing habitable worlds for a civilisation that collapsed centuries ago. Its final entries describe a planet of remarkable promise — and the coordinates are within our reach. The cultural archive absorbs everything: alien poetry, star maps, a last message to a family that no longer exists.",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice2_text": "Salvage the entire vessel for parts",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice2_outcome": "The boarding team strips the alien ship methodically. Its hull alloys are decades ahead of ours. Its power cells still hold charge. The alien is given a burial in space — set adrift toward the nearest star. The Exodus is stronger for the encounter, if a little haunted.",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice3_text": "Leave it undisturbed — this is a grave",
  "event_deadAlienArtifact_choice3_outcome": "The captain records the coordinates and broadcasts a memorial signal on all frequencies. The crew is sombre but unified. Something about honouring a fellow traveller — even an alien one — reminds everyone why they're out here.",
  "event_repairStation_title": "The Relay Station",
  "event_repairStation_narrative": "Sensors detect a massive structure orbiting a burnt-out dwarf star — an automated repair station, still operational after what must be millennia. Its docking clamps extend as we approach, and a synthetic voice broadcasts in a hundred languages, the last of which is a stilted, mathematical English: \"VESSEL DETECTED. SYSTEMS DEGRADED. REPAIR PROTOCOLS AVAILABLE. EXCHANGE REQUIRED.\" The station's manifest lists services and prices in universal resource units. It will trade, but it will not give.",
  "event_repairStation_choice0_text": "Trade probes for a full ship overhaul",
  "event_repairStation_choice0_outcome": "The station's repair drones swarm the Exodus in a ballet of precision welding and circuit replacement. Hull breaches sealed, navigation recalibrated, scanners restored. When they withdraw, the ship feels new. The probe bay, however, is empty.",
  "event_repairStation_choice1_text": "Spend fuel to repair critical systems only",
  "event_repairStation_choice1_outcome": "The station accepts fuel rods as payment and focuses on the worst-damaged systems. The work is fast and flawless. The fuel gauge drops noticeably, but the ship will survive longer for it.",
  "event_repairStation_choice2_text": "Trade tech databases for probes and energy cells",
  "event_repairStation_choice2_outcome": "The station's AI is ravenous for data. It copies our entire technical library — engineering manuals, scientific databases, manufacturing blueprints — and in exchange fabricates fresh probes and energy cells from raw materials. The tech archive is diminished, but the supplies are invaluable.",
  "event_repairStation_choice3_text": "Offer the cultural archive for a comprehensive refit",
  "event_repairStation_choice3_outcome": "The station broadcasts the works of Shakespeare, Bach, and a thousand other human voices into its memory banks. In return, it performs a thorough overhaul and loads the probe bays with freshly manufactured units. The cultural archive is gutted, but the ship may actually reach its destination now.",
