  "ending_epilogueGoldenAge": "Against all odds, the broadcast took root. {planetName} received humanity not as wreckage but as living seed: fertile ground, working systems, and enough strength to build beyond mere survival. Within a generation, art, science, and culture flourished. Children born on {planetName} looked up at unfamiliar stars and called them home. The voyage became the founding myth of a new civilization ready to cast its own future outward.",
  "@ending_epilogueGoldenAge": {
    "placeholders": {
      "planetName": {
        "type": "String"
      }
    }
  },
  "ending_epilogueThrivingColony": "The landing was rough, but the seed held. {planetName} proved generous enough for water to flow, crops to root, and the ship's surviving systems to be broken down into the first real settlement. By the end of the first decade, a thriving town stood where Exodus had come to rest. Humanity had not merely survived the crossing. It had begun again.",
  "@ending_epilogueThrivingColony": {
    "placeholders": {
      "planetName": {
        "type": "String"
      }
    }
  },
  "ending_epilogueSurvival": "Survival was never guaranteed, and on {planetName} every day had to be earned. The damaged ship provided only the barest essentials, but the seed did not die in transit. Colonists adapted through stubbornness and ingenuity, carving a future from a world that offered little freely. Later generations would remember the hardship of the founding years and the resolve that kept the broadcast alive.",
  "@ending_epilogueSurvival": {
    "placeholders": {
      "planetName": {
        "type": "String"
      }
    }
  },
  "ending_epilogueStruggling": "The colony clung to existence like seed scattered onto bad soil. {planetName} was unforgiving, resources were thin, and the ship's degraded systems offered little help. Rationing became a way of life. Some whispered that Exodus should have flown on. Still, the settlement endured: diminished, hardened, and unwilling to die quietly.",
  "@ending_epilogueStruggling": {
    "placeholders": {
      "planetName": {
        "type": "String"
      }
    }
  },
  "ending_epilogueDire": "The landing on {planetName} was a disaster. Critical ship systems failed during descent, and what should have been a sowing became a crash. Within months, the colony was reduced to a handful of desperate survivors sheltering in the ship's wreckage. Whether they would last another year was uncertain. The final log closed with a single line: \"We are still here. For now.\"",
  "@ending_epilogueDire": {
    "placeholders": {
      "planetName": {
        "type": "String"
      }
    }
  },
  "ending_epilogueExtinction": "The broadcast ended on {planetName}. The distress beacon continued to pulse long after the last colonist drew breath, but the seed never took root. The ship's black box recorded everything: the failing systems, the desperate final days, and the silence that followed. If another vessel ever finds this world, it will know that humanity tried to scatter life among the stars, and failed here.",
  "@ending_epilogueExtinction": {
    "placeholders": {
      "planetName": {
        "type": "String"
      }
    }
  },
  "ending_epilogueDefault": "The voyage is over. What comes next is up to the survivors.",
